<title>Jan_1993: Re: Suicide and Adventism</title>
<h1>Re: Suicide and Adventism</h1>
Ralf Simonsson (<i>/G=Ralf/S=Simonsson/O=Fimnet/@elisa.fi</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 20 Jan 1993 06:27:41 +0200</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#75">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#75">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#75">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#75">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0076.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: Suicide and Adventism"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0074.html">Steven Timm: "Care for the Dying"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0060.html">Ralf Simonsson: "Suicide and Adventism"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0076.html">Marcus Stringer: "Re: Suicide and Adventism"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt; But I wonder if </i><br>
<i>&gt;&gt; adventism puts such a pressure on people so they do not find any </i><br>
other <br>
<i>&gt;&gt; solution than destroy their lives?</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;What kind of unique problems can you suggest? suicide</i><br>
<i>&gt;are not unique to the SDA faith, nor are they necessarily due to one's </i><br>
church<br>
<i>&gt;membership. </i><br>
I think there should not be these kind of problems (shame, sweeping sins <br>
under the mat, unforgiveness) in the church - we are on our way to <br>
heaven aren4t we?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;&gt; things with - because suicide does not exist among belivers!</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Among the pastors that I am closely acquainted with, I have not found</i><br>
<i>&gt;such denial </i><br>
I see - you have solved all your problems! But there still exists <br>
members in the church who are not as fortunate.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;If you believe (perhaps because you were taught) that these things save </i><br>
you,<br>
<i>&gt;that they are of primary importance; if that's all you heard as you </i><br>
grew up,<br>
<i>&gt;yes, indeed, you're life would have pressures.  The foundation is always</i><br>
<i>&gt;a personal relationship with God.  When it's impersonal, you're in </i><br>
tough shape.<br>
<i>&gt;Any Christian subculture (not unique to Adventism, I can assure you) has</i><br>
<i>&gt;pressures to conform.  So, if the "model Adventist" person is doing the</i><br>
<i>&gt;"right" things on the outside but is rebellious (or at least confused) </i><br>
on<br>
<i>&gt;the inside, that can lead to mental problems.  Note especially that the</i><br>
<i>&gt;causes of depression and suicide are multitudinous.</i><br>
Now we come to the point -  how can we make our christianity real; so <br>
that it will eliminate all these causes for depression instead for <br>
increasing them!<br>
<p>
May be your finnish pastor knows me - if he has been in Finland since <br>
the 604s - if so, my greetings and God bless you.<br>
<p>
Ralf Simonsson<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
