In the week since I put out the directory, we've gained twelve new<br>
subscriptions.  It worked so well I'm going to try it again.<br>
I would like to reach at least 200 subscriptions by the end of this year,<br>
and I think we can do it.  Those SDAnet people who wonder "What are<br>
these wierd messages marked SDA-L that I can't reply to?"  For 32 people<br>
signed up to SDA-L, this is all they get.  Most of them don't want the<br>
high traffic of SDAnet or else they would be signed up.  Some of them<br>
may not yet have heard about the weekly digest in which all messages<br>
come once a week, but they can contact me if they need to do this.<br>
<p>
<p>
The directory follows:<br>
<p>
SDA-L and SDAnet membership information as of Jan 15 1993<br>
<p>
This information is for SDA-L and SDAnet members usage only.  Misuse will<br>
not be tolerated.<br>
<p>
116 working addresses are signed up to SDAnet right now, and 32 other working<br>
addresses are signed up to SDA-L but not SDAnet.  5 are signed up to<br>
the SDAnet Digest.<br>
<p>
Any directory changes or questions about either list should go to me.<br>
