<title>Jan_1993: inspiration</title>
<h1>inspiration</h1>
Sherman Cox (<i>scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 22 Jan 93 13:46:14 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#89">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#89">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#89">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#89">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0090.html">Fred Christiansen: "sources for OnLine Bible (excellent PC freeware)"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0088.html">Steven Timm: "SDA-L: Updated Directory, one more time"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0085.html">Steve Hix: "Re: inspiration"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I believe one thing that really needs to be done as a first step in<br>
religious discussion is to be truthfull with others and to be truthfull<br>
with ourselves.  One thing is that no matter how fundamentalist you think<br>
you are you still interpret the Bible.  I guess I should say I have yet to meet<br>
someone who takes the Bible litterally in everything it says.  When pressed most<br>
people will admit the need to interpret at least portions of the Bible.  <br>
<p>
I am reminded of the text that says women should keep silent in church.<br>
We interpret that text.  We do not take it litterally as it reads.   We<br>
should interpret that text.  We should take a lot of things into consideration<br>
when we make doctrine.  Things such as Time, place, who was the being talked to.<br>
I say all this because some of us deify our interpretations and make them<br>
the Bible.  Therefore since it is the Bible we fight all who disagree with them as <br>
heretics.  Don't miss my point I am not talking of the place of women in the<br>
church.<br>
<p>
Because we must interpret there is an even greater need for the Holy Spirit<br>
to guide us as we study Truth and the things of Truth.  <br>
<pre>
-- 
<p>
"All things are possible to him that believeth."
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II       scox@uahcs2.cs.uah.edu
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
