<title>Jan_1993: Rejoice with me for my house has passed final inspection!</title>
<h1>Rejoice with me for my house has passed final inspection!</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 27 Jan 93 13:07:12 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#118">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#118">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#118">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#118">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0119.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: KJV - historical Adventist's bible"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0117.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "KJV - historical Adventist's bible"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the spirit of Matt 18 and Luke 15, I wish to share my joy that my<br>
build-it-yourself house just passed final inspection this morning.<br>
I have been putting in late hours working on the house, missing time<br>
with my family, and feeling incredibly frustrated when certain<br>
plumbing fixtures refused to stop leaking no matter what I did<br>
over a period of several days.  I tho't I had come up with the final<br>
fixes yesterday, so called for final.  Last night had its share<br>
of frustrations and I still had not completed 3 things which were<br>
required for final.<br>
<p>
Having already spent too long in a small rental with a family of 4 kids<br>
and wife who was going bananas, last night I was about feeling that the Lord<br>
had forgotten us in our distress, that surely we would flunk final.<br>
But the Lord showed He's in control.  The inspector who came was the<br>
one we've developed goodwill with and he winked at the 3 problems,<br>
knowing we'll fix 'em, he said, and signed off the final.<br>
<p>
Whoopee! and Praise the Lord!  It's been a long time coming.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
