Hi all,<br>
<p>
Tony writes :<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt;I have often wondered why certain elements of the church are so opposed</i><br>
<i>&gt;to the use of the newer, more accurate translations of the bible. </i><br>
<p>
I would disagree with you here Tony, what evidence is there to support<br>
this claim that the newer translations are more accurate ? In fact I would<br>
argue the opposite considering that almost all of the new translations<br>
come directly from Jesuit scholars and are based on texts which belong<br>
in the same family as the Latin Vulgate. <br>
<p>
All those interested in assertaining whether or not there still is any<br>
merit in the KJV compared to the newer translations should read<br>
"Our Authorised Bible Vindicated" (by Andreason ?) some time.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Could it be because the KJV supports some of the distinctive SDA doctrines</i><br>
<i>&gt;well, whereas other translations may not?</i><br>
<p>
I wonder why this would be so ? :)<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;The main examples which come to mind are "2300 days" (KJV) versus "2300</i><br>
<i>&gt;evening-mornings" or "2300 evenings and mornings" (NIV etc.), and also</i><br>
