<title>Jan_1993: Re: health</title>
<h1>Re: health</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 28 Jan 93 12:13:17 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#120">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#120">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#120">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#120">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0121.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Inspiration"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0119.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: KJV - historical Adventist's bible"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0093.html">Sherman Cox: "health"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0127.html">Sherman Cox: "Re: health"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Hi all,<br>
<p>
Sherman H. Cox, II writes :<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; I was wondering if anyone out there has any thoughts on the Adventist</i><br>
<i>&gt; Health message calling us to be at the front of the conservation, </i><br>
<i>&gt; anti-polution, andti-poverty movements.  I ask this because a lot of</i><br>
<i>&gt; health problems stem from the envirement we live in.</i><br>
<p>
<p>
Well lets see in our list of priorities as the remnant church what should<br>
be our number one priority ?<br>
<p>
1) conservation<br>
2) anti-polution<br>
3) anti-poverty<br>
4) anti-war<br>
5) anti-nuclear<br>
6) what ever you feel anti about<br>
<p>
7) proclaiming the judgment message (3 angels) and preparing the world for<br>
the advent and the end of all things. (which includes the end of war, and of <br>
poverty, and polution AND the end of the ecology.)<br>
<p>
It seems to me some of us would like to stay on this earth for a long time to <br>
come. No thanks, get me out of here and into heaven. This world is not my home,<br>
we are to be pilgrims and wanderers upon the earth, are we not ?<br>
<p>
We forget that the reason for the ecology going down the tubes and poverty<br>
(mainly due to famine and greed) is because of the curse of sin which is<br>
upon the earth which will not dissipate not matter what we do but will increase<br>
until the final day. <br>
<p>
How about instead of putting the symptoms in 1st priority we treat the cause <br>
of the disease first. No we shouldn't ignore these things but as people living<br>
in the last days shouldn't we be hastening the Lord's coming ? Or do we say<br>
"the Lord delayeth His coming all things continue..." ?<br>
<p>
You know inspiration tells us that the Lord would have come a long time ago<br>
and put an end to these things, but we as a people and individually like the <br>
Jews have been unprepared for His coming. The scripture tells us that this is <br>
reason why the Lord has delayed His coming (for over 100 years now) because He <br>
wishes none to be lost. Instead of focusing on the things of this world so much<br>
why don't we do our utmost to hasten His coming. ?<br>
<p>
That will bring the ultimate solution to these problems we see around us.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
