<title>Jan_1993: If the KJV was good enough for Ellen G. White, it's good enough for me!</title>
<h1>If the KJV was good enough for Ellen G. White, it's good enough for me!</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 27 Jan 1993 23:21:09 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#123">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#123">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#123">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#123">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0124.html">PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au: "Historical Adventism and the environment"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0122.html">Steven Timm: "Inspiration"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0130.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: If the KJV was good enough for Ellen G. White, it's good enough for me!"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Ah, but here's the trap.  The KJV wasn't good enough for Ellen G. White.<br>
 Many times in her writings she quotes from the Revised Version, which<br>
was the only other version available in her time.  <br>
<p>
In all fairness, we should say that some of the modern paraphrases of the <br>
Bible do major damage to the meaning of Romans and other books.  On the <br>
other hand, some of the newer versions, NIV for instance, do a much better<br>
job in setting forth the chronological order in Genesis 1 and 2  (some <br>
net.theologians would claim they did a hatchet job.)<br>
<p>
For myself, the KJV is still the only study Bible I own.  I have the NIV<br>
on computer, and for reading I use the New American Standard Bible and the <br>
New Revised Standard Version.<br>
<p>
Since we have many people on this net who are not blessed (or cursed)<br>
with many different translations of the Bible in their language, it would<br>
be interesting to hear how the various Adventist doctrines translate into<br>
other languages.  I know from personal experience that they translate into<br>
Afrikaans rather well.  Does every Adventist in South America learn that <br>
the two-horned beast of Revelation 13 is the United States, for instance?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
