Ruben Gonzalez writes:<br>
[ ... ]<br>
<i>&gt;In fact I find the whole thing a little worrying. The reason is because</i><br>
<i>&gt;we the SDA church should have been at the front of the health message, but</i><br>
<i>&gt;due to our wilful neglect of the message, others have taken up the banners</i><br>
<i>&gt;we should be carrying. To the point that the work that Gods people should</i><br>
<i>&gt;have been at the front of Satan has taken over and his people -- the New Age</i><br>
<i>&gt;Movement is now at the forefront. That's right go into any health food shop</i><br>
<i>&gt;and look around. And you know, a lot of people are coming to the new age </i><br>
<i>&gt;movement through, *our* health message. Healthy living these days is almost </i><br>
<i>&gt;always associated with spiritism and the new age. How very sad for the church </i><br>
<i>&gt;that we have allowed Satan to steal our secret weapon because we couldn't </i><br>
<i>&gt;care less.</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;And what's worse is that while we have allowed Satan to steal our weapons,</i><br>
<i>&gt;the movement we should be in front of, we in turn are now trying to steal</i><br>
<i>&gt;his weapon and the movements that his followers (spiritists) have been in front</i><br>
<i>&gt;of for a long time. Really, just ten years ago a greenie = a spiritist.</i><br>
<p>
Why should the fact that some other groups share some of our beliefs be<br>
a major concern to us?  We don't have a a mortgage on truth do we?  If<br>
someone shares some of our beliefs, that should make it easier to reach them.<br>
<p>
IMHO, caring for the environment is as important as caring for<br>
ourselves.  Perhaps even more important, because it is saying to other<br>
people that we care about them and don't want to harm what is just as<br>
much their environment as it is ours.  This argument applies even more<br>
strongly to the other "priorities" raised: anti-poverty, anti-war,<br>
etc.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Whats happened ? have we switched camps or something ?</i><br>
<p>
Maybe we are realising that we are somewhat defficient in some areas (but perhaps<br>
slipping in others ...)?<br>
