<title>Jan_1993: Undergraduate Teaching Position - Columbia Union College</title>
<h1>Undergraduate Teaching Position - Columbia Union College</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 29 Jan 1993 10:51:39 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#144">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#144">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#144">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#144">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0145.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Bible versions"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0143.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Getting files from the server..."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[From Sue Harrington   ( sue@cuc.edu)]<br>
I have been reading SDA net for a couple of years and have not been an<br>
active part of the discussion though I read most of them.  At the end of<br>
this school year I will be leaving Columbia Union College where I have<br>
served as the coordinator and professor of computer science.  We have<br>
approximately 50 majors in computer science.  We have a laboratory that<br>
includes five Sun ELC's, one SLC, three 3B2's, 20 pc's--286`s. 386's,<br>
and 486's.  We have an active student chapter of the ACM.  For the last<br>
two years we have had a grant from the National Science Foundation to<br>
attract and retain undergraduate women in the study of computer science.<br>
 In the advanced Data Structures course this year we have six women and<br>
one man.  We are also concentrating on attracting African-American and<br>
Latino persons.  We also appear to be making an impact in this area.  <br>
<p>
We are looking for someone with a Ph.D. in computer science or a closely<br>
related field to come to Columbia Union College to replace me.  We want<br>
to encourage women and persons from groups other than the dominant one<br>
to apply, as well as others who are committed to passing on a knowledge<br>
of computer science.  You should have excellent teaching skills.  <br>
<p>
Takoma Park is a wonderful place to live.  We live on Sligo Creek<br>
Parkway, a couple of miles of school.  We can walk two different ways to<br>
work, both through parks.  We can run seven miles on running trails in<br>
one direction and two miles in the other direction.  We have an<br>
excellent track across the park from our condominium we one could do<br>
speed training.  What I am trying to say is if you think that urban<br>
living is undesirable you owe it to yourself to come to Washington, D.C.<br>
and see for yourself what a wonderful city it is.  On the weekends we do<br>
urban hiking through parks in the city to our hearts' content.<br>
<p>
If you are interested or know or someone who might be interested in this<br>
job please send me e-mail:  sue@cuc.edu or you could call the head of<br>
the Mathematical Sciences Department, Dr. Pauline David, Columbia Union<br>
College, 7600 Flower Avenue, Takoma Park, MD 20912 (301) 891-4171.  <br>
<p>
Looking forward to hearing from you,<br>
<p>
Sue Harrington<br>
sue@cuc.edu<br>
<p>
<p>
[Where are you going, Sue?  SCT]<br>
