<title>Jan_1993: The cure for the evil on this earth</title>
<h1>The cure for the evil on this earth</h1>
cheryl berthelsen (<i>cherylb@csd4.csd.uwm.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Sat, 30 Jan 93 00:15:37 -0600</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#146">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#146">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#146">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#146">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0147.html">ARKUSINSKI ANDY : "PERSONAL INFO"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0145.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Bible versions"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I was recently reading a psychology book entitled "The tyranny of malice:<br>
A study of the dark side of character and culture."  The author, Joseph<br>
Berke, states that most of the evil on this earth (both personal and<br>
national) are an expressions of three basic human emotions--envy, greed,<br>
and jealousy.  He presents various philosophies on how to deal with these<br>
negative emotions and why they won't work.  After 400 pages of very<br>
depressing reading of the very nature of these controlling forces, he<br>
ends with just 4 pages of solution.  (The correct solution, I believe, IMHO).<br>
He says there are three oppositves of envy, greed, and jealousy that are the<br>
only hope for eradicating evil from our personal thoughts and lives as well<br>
as the evil in community, family, and nation.  The cure is--GRATITUDE,<br>
GENEROSITY, and COMPASSION.  What a better world this would be if every<br>
person appreciated the bountious blessings given, showed that appreciation<br>
through generosity towards others, and served one another with compassionate<br>
service!  Isn't that the life Jesus Christ live?  Isn't that the life that<br>
His disciples should should live?  I pray that each one of us may pray for<br>
a greater measure of His Spirit to enable us to life that way!<br>
<p>
Cheryl<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
