<title>Aug_1992: Re: Subculture,Superculture, or Counterculture?</title>
<h1>Re: Subculture,Superculture, or Counterculture?</h1>
Paul Gates (<i>70516.420@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>11 Aug 92 08:08:32 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#6">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#6">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#6">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#6">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0007.html">cheryl berthelsen: "SDA subculture"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0005.html">Bill Nickless: "Subculture,Superculture, or Counterculture?"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0005.html">Bill Nickless: "Subculture,Superculture, or Counterculture?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve, Just a couple of sidelights on your comments. It has been my<br>
experience that the Adventist heros never mention that they are Adventists<br>
to the world. We are the only ones that know it, it appears. -- I am<br>
talking about interviews, etc. on tv and radio. Perhaps it is a good idea<br>
to have it that way when heros become un-heros.<br>
<p>
The other comment has slipped my mind, so I will have to add it later!!<br>
<p>
I have deposited a little money at Andrews as a result of 3 children<br>
attending there. They tell me it was a "jungle" -- they compared it to<br>
Jackson Prison, Steve. -- not because of the faculty or the so called<br>
system but because of the riff-raft who were allowed to attend Andrews. 2<br>
of my children did get out of Andrews and still remain Adventists, 1<br>
didn't.<br>
<p>
I realize that this probably has nothing to do with what you are talking<br>
about Steve. I get ansi when we say we are using the same traditional ways<br>
in our colleges in particular. They do not work!<br>
<p>
When I drive on an Academy or College campus I get that "funny feeling" in<br>
the pit of my stomach still! I think of the way I was treated as well as<br>
my children when we were in school.<br>
<p>
I do not think I am repeating myself but I can give an example to let you<br>
know where I am coming from.<br>
<p>
My son was in the school band, they had been gone this particular Sabbath<br>
to a church in the area to present a program. The "uniform" was turtle<br>
neck sweater, matching slacks and sport coat. When they got back to the<br>
school in the late afternoon they did not have time enough to change<br>
clothes. They went to vespers and my son with two others (trumpet trio)<br>
had been asked to play for special music. Nothing was said to the boys<br>
prior to their playing by the faculty in charge.<br>
<p>
As soon as the vesper program was over the 3 boys were taken "in hand" by<br>
a couple of the faculty members and said since they did not wear a dress<br>
shirt and tie to Vespers they could not perform in the band concert that<br>
evening and would be confined to their rooms.<br>
<p>
My wife and I + our other children were there when this happened and<br>
witnessed all this because we were there for the evening concert. At that<br>
point I "butted" into the conversation and said that they might restrict<br>
him from playing in the concert but he was not going to be confined to his<br>
room since we were there. I checked with the principal and I had his<br>
support. We went out to supper that evening and had as good of a time as<br>
we could as a family.<br>
<p>
Years later, after my son had left the church, he received a letter from<br>
both of these faculty member's stating that they wanted to apologize for<br>
their actions for they had really been out to get my son and they knew<br>
what they had done was wrong.<br>
<p>
Some on the net may think that was an exception to the rule but it wasn't<br>
I could tell you some horror stories that happened to my 2 daughters which<br>
were really ridiculous because it was over petty, non-essential stuff that<br>
would turn a seasoned adult away.<br>
<p>
I am not blaming Adelphian Academy, Andrews University for the attitude of<br>
my grown children today, I realize that young people still make their own<br>
decisions and in my son's case he could have chosen to do things<br>
differently and be wiser in choice of friends.<br>
<p>
I have pastored several academy churches, was an associate pastor at<br>
Southern College and I can assure you that my expertize of ministry is<br>
not at an "Adventist Ghetto."<br>
<p>
Evelyn (my wife) and I were discussing just the other day, we do not want<br>
to retire, (if we ever do) at an Adventist Ghetto. We would prefer to<br>
live where there is no Adventist church -- A place where we can get<br>
acquainted with the town people, associate with them, socialize with them<br>
and eventually begin a Bible study group and teach the gospel as it is in<br>
Jesus. If we could plant a church that would be great. That is our goal.<br>
<p>
till next time, Steve,<br>
<p>
...........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
