<title>Aug_1992: Fails miserably?</title>
<h1>Fails miserably?</h1>
Tony (<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 13 Aug 1992 18:42 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#13">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#13">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#13">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#13">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0014.html">Steven Timm: "Vocational training at Adventist colleges"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0012.html">Bill Nickless: "measuring SDA school success"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0024.html">Bill Nickless: "Fails miserably?"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I've been following the discussion regarding Adventist education and<br>
institutions with interest, and one thing which has come across very<br>
strongly is this conclusion that SDA schools are not "working" at all.<br>
<p>
It seems to me that some of you guys are viewing the system as a "system",<br>
and not as a collection of individuals - which is what it is.<br>
<p>
By stating that they system is not working, are you criticizing the<br>
teachers in the schools? The school administrators? The school governing<br>
bodies? The church administrators? Adventists in general? Where do you<br>
see the failing link?<br>
<p>
Of course, in the above list I didn't even mention the students themselves.<br>
I don't think it is fair to talk about students as being the "product of<br>
the system" as if they were passive participants in the process. The students<br>
themselves are a part of the system, and they must take the responsibility<br>
for their own decisions.<br>
<p>
I went to an Adventist high school and college here in Australia, and <br>
am now completing my B.Sc.(Hons) at a State university. I don't think<br>
I can agree that Adventist education "failed miserably" in the case<br>
of myself and most of my friends.<br>
<p>
Let the discussion continue...<br>
<p>
Tony Dyson<br>
University of Newcastle<br>
Australia<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
