<!-- body="start" -->
Cheryl listed a laundry list of vocational and technical training<br>
programs that maybe SDA colleges or even academies could offer.<br>
These included auto body, small business administration, cosmetology,<br>
construction technology, and others.  The above and other like programs<br>
are all available as 1 or 2 yr degrees from Andrews University.<br>
(with the exception of cosmetology which Andrews has a program with a <br>
local beauty school so that students can stay at Andrews but study<br>
at the beauty place--expensive but some people do it.)<br>
<p>
Andrews at one time had non-degree programs in these areas aimed more at<br>
the non-traditional college student, but the problem they found is <br>
that often students would want to do more college after this and the<br>
credits were not transferrable into a degree program.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
