Bill's idea to put an SDA dorm at Urbana-Champaign is not a new idea.<br>
In fact, a similar idea is in process, and has been going for a couple<br>
years at Michigan State.  The East Lansing church recently bought a new<br>
church building, which came with a parsonage that their pastor didn't use.<br>
So they converted it to housing for MSU students, they have five the last I <br>
checked, all female.  They call it "Sigma Delta Alpha"  (and convieniently<br>
there is not a national fraternity by that name).<br>
