<title>Aug_1992: Individuals are responsible</title>
<h1>Individuals are responsible</h1>
Russell Grau (<i>reg@ctsx.celtech.com</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 13 Aug 92 09:39 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#22">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#22">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#22">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#22">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0023.html">Stan Macasieb: "Re: measuring SDA school success"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0021.html">Russell Grau: "Individuals are responsible"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Steve Timm Writes:<br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt; (Comments about "real world" deleted) - good, well thought post Steve....</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;In the post-institutional world, we are not out debating on the street</i><br>
<i>&gt;corner how much percent of which flavor of Divine nature Christ had.  We</i><br>
<i>&gt;face the question of whether He existed at all from our non-Christian friends.</i><br>
<i>&gt;We face not semantics over righteousness by faith but the question of </i><br>
<i>&gt;whom one should have faith in. </i><br>
<p>
AMEN!!  More and more of the people that I work with and my friends are part<br>
of the new pagan movement - the New Age.  Service takes on a new meaning when<br>
speaking with them.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;Elmhurst SDA church is only five miles from Hinsdale and the large "SDA"</i><br>
<i>&gt;hospital and associated church.  Of the seven youth in my class, two</i><br>
<i>&gt;have a parent who works for the hospital, two are children of the pastor.</i><br>
<i>&gt;But even at that, the superstructure of the church has no impact on them</i><br>
<i>&gt;except for the indirect financial one.  Most of them have never seen </i><br>
<i>&gt;Andrews University, let alone considered going there.  Though we are </i><br>
<i>&gt;only 30 miles away from Broadview Academy, no youth from our church attend,</i><br>
<i>&gt;and only one of the seven is in the local day school.  The church to them</i><br>
<i>&gt;is the local church only.  And although they complain sometimes that</i><br>
<i>&gt;we don't get together more with other churches, they often miss the </i><br>
<i>&gt;activities that are planned.</i><br>
<p>
In my youth class at Rio Linda SDA Church in Rio Linda, California, we had on<br>
average 6 youth (in a church with an average attendence during Sabbath school<br>
of only 35 - 40 on good days).  Of these 6 youth, only 1 attended our schools.<br>
Of the 15 to 25 or so youth that attended our church (cradle roll -&gt; teen) I <br>
can recall that only 3 or 4 attended the church schools.<br>
<p>
Most families could not afford it.  Their children attended public schools.  In<br>
our youth group, we had several teens that smoked (their parents didn't know),<br>
one teen engaging in severe at-risk behaviour.  Several others thinking about<br>
one form or another of at-risk behaviour if not actually participating at one<br>
time or another.<br>
<p>
Those that did attend the church school wanted to go to the larger churches<br>
because that is where their friends went.  <br>
<p>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;In my mind this is the disadvantage that comes as the administration</i><br>
<i>&gt;disintegrates under its own weight.  I want our young people to be able</i><br>
<i>&gt;to see that they are part of a larger, exciting, whole.  In the Chicago</i><br>
<i>&gt;area there are 800 baptized young people in the Illinois conference</i><br>
<i>&gt;churches, and probably an equal number in the Lake Region conference</i><br>
<i>&gt;churches.  Less than 150 of those attend Broadview Academy.  What structure </i><br>
<i>&gt;is our church going to establish for the other 75% of its youth?</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<p>
I think this is one that you need to get the youth involved with.  Recently, <br>
our church in Bellevue, Washington had two nights where we met together and<br>
discussed where the church was headed.  ALL the youth were invited to <br>
participate.  Several of the more out-spoken showed up for both nights.<br>
<p>
Their voice carried the same weight as an adults.  (One person one vote <br>
principal applied, HEAVILY)  As a result of these meetings, a church committee<br>
was formed to implement the results of our reactions to the Valuegenesis<br>
study.  YOUTH are the committee's only concern.  I am hoping that this will<br>
help to prepare our church to actually reach those youth who are attending<br>
public schools and make it easier for them to invite their friends to our<br>
church.<br>
<p>
Who knows?  More updates as they happen.....<br>
<p>
<i>&gt;Steve Timm</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<i>&gt;</i><br>
<p>
