<title>Aug_1992: Modesty</title>
<h1>Modesty</h1>
Tony (<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 20 Aug 1992 15:52 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#32">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#32">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#32">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#32">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0033.html">Tony: "Re: Adventist Education"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Paul Johnston: "Re: measuring SDA school success"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I don't like to see an extreme case dictate the way we act in "normal"<br>
situations.<br>
<p>
Neither do I like to see our normal kinds of judgments applied to extreme<br>
cases.<br>
<p>
"Sunbathing in the nude" is not an issue in Adventist academies in<br>
Australia, and I wouldn't expect that it is in the U.S.  The kinds of<br>
dress issues we face are things like jewellery +/-, wearing sleeveless<br>
shirts/singlet tops to class, skirt length , and, to a lesser extent,<br>
makeup.<br>
<p>
I agree that modesty often relates very much to the surrounding culture.<br>
 From what I've heard, the only women wearing jewellery in Bible times<br>
were prostitutes. This is no longer the case. Hence I can see good reasons<br>
why modest women in Bible times would not wear jewellery. The same reasons<br>
do not apply today.<br>
<p>
If a guy wears an earring in his left ear, it is supposed to indicate<br>
heterosexual promiscuity (as far as I know). As long as this is the case,<br>
a modest guy wouldn't wear an earring in his left ear.<br>
<p>
Surely modesty is all about the statements your appearance makes to those<br>
you come into contact with. It is the interpretation others make of the<br>
way you present yourself that is important. Hence if I came to the USA<br>
for a holiday I wouldn't wear my wedding ring to an Adventist church.<br>
Perhaps if I went to Germany I might sunbake nude!<br>
<p>
Then again, a sunburnt nose is one thing.....<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<p>
P.S. When I was in academy we weren't allowed to wear jeans on Saturday<br>
afternoons (or shorts, actually).<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0033.html">Tony: "Re: Adventist Education"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0031.html">Paul Johnston: "Re: measuring SDA school success"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
