<title>Aug_1992: Re: drug money</title>
<h1>Re: drug money</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 25 Aug 92 9:27:39 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#45">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#45">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#45">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#45">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0046.html">Tony: "The minister's wife - what's her name again?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0044.html">Steven Timm: "Family Values in the SDA church"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
[McCluskey G writes:]<br>
<i>&gt; The main campus library at Loma Linda University is named after a</i><br>
<i>&gt; casino developer (Del Webb) who gave some money to the university.</i><br>
<i>&gt; It's impractical to trace the origins of money to any depth, but I do</i><br>
<i>&gt; think this goes too far.</i><br>
<p>
Del Webb was (I believe he's dead now) a real estate developer.  Casinos<br>
represent a rather modest portion of his vast enterprises.  Several<br>
huge retirement towns (Sun City, Sun City West, et al) exist in Arizona,<br>
all developed by Del Webb.  There are also many other Del Webb subdivisions<br>
in this area as well as hotels, etc.  Plus he had similar real estate dev'ts<br>
in California, Nevada, and several other states.<br>
<p>
I heard he attended Adventist schools (FOAF stories, you know) altho<br>
never an SDA (similar to the chap who flew around the world non-stop).<br>
<p>
It would be interesting to study what Scripture and EGW have to say on<br>
what to do when money is received by church entities from questionable<br>
sources.  ADRA/Ingathering money may be a somewhat different issue, btw.<br>
<p>
I recall, when a child, going with my father to various movie moguls<br>
in India to canvas them for Uplift (as Ingathering was called there); their<br>
donations were quite generous, several thousand dollars worth of rupees.<br>
India, btw, produces far more movies than Hollywood ever dreamed of.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  On Attitude &amp; the Immune System:  A sound heart is the life of the flesh:
    but envy the rottenness of the bones.  Prov 14:30
</pre>
