<title>Aug_1992: Re: Who's in Charge?</title>
<h1>Re: Who's in Charge?</h1>
Daniel D Deavours (<i>ddd42961@uxa.cso.uiuc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 27 Aug 92 15:04:29 CDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#59">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#59">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#59">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#59">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0060.html">Tony: "Re: Who's in charge?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0058.html">Bill Nickless: "Who's in charge?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;Let's talk about beating the system.</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;There exists (last I knew) a rule at Andrews University that by default, any</i><br>
<i>&gt;undergraduate student less than 22 years of age must live in the dormitory and</i><br>
<i>&gt;purchase a meal plan from the cafeteria.  The only acceptable exceptions to</i><br>
<i>&gt;this policy are derived from having a family member (older than 25) to live</i><br>
<i>&gt;with.</i><br>
<p>
	Since we may as well be honset, here it goes.  I'm a student at the<br>
University of Illinois (Champaign-Urbana) and am quite happy with the program<br>
I'm in.  All my SDA friends have either gone to an SDA academy and/or college.<br>
I honestly considered taking a semester off and attending quarter (right?) at<br>
Andrews, taking anything that would transfer.  I thought it would be an<br>
excellent opportunity to meet people, faculty, and take a religion course.<br>
	In talking with a rescent graduate I learned of this rule.  Having been<br>
fed up living in a box and eating (sometimes gross) food, I decided that I<br>
would never live in a dorm again if I could help it.<br>
	Having learned of that rule, that option went from an "expensive<br>
alternative" to an "out of the question."  (I'm rather outspoken about this,<br>
so excuse me if I come on a little strong.)<br>
	I'm 20 years old, and I'm old enough to:<br>
Vote<br>
Die for my country<br>
Receive the death penalty<br>
Sit on a jurey<br>
Get married<br>
Be a deacon at the local church<br>
	But apparently I'm not old enough to live in my own apartment (which<br>
is where I'm writing this post right now.)  It's that rule in particular that<br>
is keeping me from attending classes there this semseter.  Those rules are<br>
not trivial, I hope people realize.<br>
<p>
Dan Deavours<br>
zeos@uiuc.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
