<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;    p.s.  I think there's something fundamentally flawed with the system</i><br>
<i>&gt;    when so many mothers *have* to work in order to send the kids the</i><br>
<i>&gt;    church school.  God has solutions if we'll seek for them.</i><br>
<p>
There are other plans out there.  My father works at a Junior academy where the<br>
'All member plan' is used.  All children in a particular church are supported<br>
tuition-wise by the church.  Each member is asked to contribute to this support,<br>
(particularly those who have children attending, but all as well, as we are all<br>
a church family!).  This is a relatively new plan, and it is hard to get complete<br>
support for, but it has reaped good results so far.  For example, a couple <br>
single parents have been able to enroll their children in the SDA school.<br>
How long it will fly largely depends on the support of the congregation, but, <br>
for what it's worth, this is an alternative...<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"If God is for us, who can be against us?"            Lisa Parry
--Romans 8:31, last sentence                   parry@andrews.edu
</pre>
