<!-- body="start" -->
To Network:<br>
<p>
I read with interest, Bob Moynihan's response to rules and culture.<br>
Idealistically I think a church has the right to expect its members to<br>
follow their biblical teachings. However, the rub comes when each<br>
denomination has it own traditions.<br>
<p>
We could carry the attitude that no one has a right to tell me what is<br>
moral to immoral extremes. The judge in Fla. reviewed the album of 2 Live<br>
Crew. As you may recall the title of the Album was "As Nasty as They<br>
Wanna Be." He declared it to be obscene and illegal. However, Dan Rather<br>
on "48 Hours" made some outlandish statements about our loss of freedoms.<br>
<p>
Geraldo Riviera had the singing group on his show. Phil Donahue and his<br>
cronies in the press threw their usual temper tantrums when the news broke<br>
and cried, "Censorship" from the roof tops.<br>
<p>
It is interesting to note that no one mentioned the lyrics!! Why? Probably<br>
because adults would be shocked and outraged by their filth and<br>
debauchery. What were the words:<br>
<p>
226 uses of the "F" word<br>
117 explicit terms for genitalia<br>
87 descriptions of oral sex<br>
163 usues of the word for the female dog<br>
15 uses of the word "Ho" (slang for whore)<br>
81 uses of the "S" word.<br>
<p>
Should we say the 2 Live Crew has the right to express themselves this<br>
way?<br>
<p>
..........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
