<!-- body="start" -->
The "all member plan" described by Lisa is just like the "Temple plan" the<br>
SDA church tried back in the 60's.  The idea was "sold" to the church because<br>
the tuition money is given to the church, the church pays the money to the<br>
school, and the parents can deduct the money from the income tax.  Our church<br>
had a real problem after the 2nd month.  There were many "dead beat" families<br>
who paid nothing but sent their kids to church school anyway, older members<br>
didn't contribute because "they already put their own kids through school."<br>
The plan collapsed under the financial burden of paying the school for kids<br>
attending with no money coming into the church to pay for it.  It was a<br>
financial nightmare for the local SDA church.<br>
<p>
cheryl<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
