<title>Oct_1992: Praying for the gift of tongues</title>
<h1>Praying for the gift of tongues</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon,  5 Oct 1992 21:32:01 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#20">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#20">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#20">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#20">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0021.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Praying for the gift of tongues"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0019.html">Steven Timm: "Re:  Discussion on perfection"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0021.html">Fred Christiansen: "Re: Praying for the gift of tongues"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
God has been moving mightily in the Pittsburgh area recently.  Within<br>
the last few months a sizable group of Spanish-speaking believers has<br>
grown<br>
within our church and we will soon begin a weekly Spanish service for them.<br>
Given Pittsburgh's almost negligible Hispanic population, this is quite<br>
an occurence.  The pastor and I are among the majority of the church members<br>
who don't speak Spanish.  <br>
<p>
SDAnet has heard before of my experience in South Africa when I prayed for <br>
the gift of tongues to learn Afrikaans, and succeeded in learning the<br>
language quickly, albeit not without study.<br>
<p>
Is this another appropriate place to pray for the gift of tongues?  Or<br>
should I, and the congregation at large, be content with the spiritual<br>
gifts we have already been given?<br>
<p>
Do people really feel that tongues, miracles, and prophecy will be <br>
part of the latter rain, or are we holding up our umbrellas for <br>
protection against it?<br>
<p>
This is an area in which I am searching myself and welcome the input<br>
from the net, from whichever direction it may come.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
