<title>Oct_1992: Family Values</title>
<h1>Family Values</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu,  1 Oct 1992 09:56:13 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#4">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#4">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#4">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#4">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0005.html">Pam Harris: "FAMILY VALUES"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0003.html">Steven Timm: "Who Warren Trenchard is, and his society"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0006.html">Bob Moynihan: "re: Family Values"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The current US Presidential election has made "Family Values" a byword in <br>
the American political scene.  However, with this thread I don't wish to <br>
focus directly on the term as defined by George Bush.  Rather, I want to <br>
explore how our church can strengthen the family.  <br>
<p>
The church I currently attend has a books membership somewhat over 200.<br>
In a brief mental survey of the families that attend the church, I can only <br>
count eight families in which both parents are members of the church and <br>
some children are still living at home and coming to church.  (This means<br>
we are most probably above average.)  A church in Illinois with which I<br>
was acquainted had a staff where all three of its ministers were currently<br>
or had been divorced.<br>
<p>
The central issue is this:  We claim that we should relate to God as a <br>
father or as a close friend.  The problem is that we do exactly that, and <br>
our dysfunctional relationships with God mirror our experience of<br>
dysfunctional relationships with families and friends.<br>
<p>
How can we increase the importance of the family in the SDA church without<br>
condemning or alienating the people who are fast becoming the majority<br>
in our church, namely singles be they those who never married, are divorced,<br>
or are single parents for whatever reason?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0005.html">Pam Harris: "FAMILY VALUES"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0003.html">Steven Timm: "Who Warren Trenchard is, and his society"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0006.html">Bob Moynihan: "re: Family Values"</a>
</ul>
