You may have noticed that shipments of messages from SDAnet have recently <br>
been arriving in only two batches a day.  I am now sending out only <br>
one batch in the morning and one batch in the evening.  It's entertaining<br>
that sometimes I get replies on them back from Australia before they <br>
have gotten across campus to my other account.<br>
<p>
We now have 95 working addresses signed up to SDAnet.  We have gotten <br>
a lot of new members recently, but also have been losing regulars due <br>
to lack of net access.  I'd like to see us break the 100-member hump.<br>
Also, somewhere during the flurry of activity last month, SDAnet sent<br>
out its 2000th message.  In today's issue of the Columbia Union Visitor<br>
there is supposed to be an article detailing SDAnet and how to sign up.<br>
Someone please let me know when you see it, because I don't currently <br>
get the Visitor.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
