<!-- body="start" -->
FYI<br>
<p>
The Andrews Society of Religious Scholars is the association of college<br>
Bible teachers at SDA colleges.  ASRS took that name so that it could<br>
be a legit group at the Society of Biblical Literature which most of<br>
the teachers were already attending.  The group meets once a year and<br>
has been functioning for some 20 years.  In spite of the opinion of some<br>
that this is a "liberal" group, and unworthy of mention, I think the group<br>
has a proper function.  There are common topics that professors of religion<br>
in SDA institutions might discuss.  Warren Trenchard, head of the religion<br>
dept. at Canadian Union College is the incoming president.  Gerald Winslow<br>
of Pacific Union College is the outgoing president.  The society's meeting<br>
will take place in San Francisco in November, just before the big meeting<br>
of the Society of Biblical Literature.<br>
<p>
 No, this society is not the same as the ATS, which only represents a small<br>
 part of the group of SDA profs. of religion.<br>
<p>
 I belong to neither organization, but am well acquainted with both.<br>
<p>
 Nancy Vyh<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
