Ruben,<br>
<p>
I've never seen a single person on SDAnet concede an inch in any doctrinal<br>
issue being discussed.  What it always turns out to be is a debate over<br>
views and attempted proofs.  When the dust settles, has anyone learned<br>
anything for the betterment of their souls?  You stated that through<br>
discussion, we learn.  I sincerely hope that it not true about spiritual<br>
matters.  It is only through personal study and instruction from the HOly<br>
Spirit that we learn truth, not discussion.<br>
<p>
I wish SDAnet could retire discussion on perfection for awhile.  It was<br>
hashed out several months ago and once again is monopolizing the bandwidth.<br>
There are many other important issues that could and should be discussed.<br>
Let's move on and give perfection a rest.<br>
<p>
Cheryl<br>
