I just feel that I should add my idea of perfection.<br>
My view of PERFECTION is that of continued CHRISTIAN MATURITY.  Whatever<br>
good is there to be done that I am aware of, I should do it.  Jesus' <br>
prayer for His disciples was that "they would be perfected even as Thou<br>
(God the Father) art perfect.  Maybe I've taken a wimpish approach to it,<br>
but for it to make sence to me, I have to interprete it as continual growth.<br>
