<p>
Well Bill, you got it in a nut shell, perfection means continual growth.<br>
This is easy to see since Jesus as a man (whom we all know was perfect)<br>
we are told "grew in grace" and that "through that which he suffered was <br>
made perfect" so we see that perfection is not a plateau that one reaches<br>
but a path that one progresses on.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
