<!-- body="start" -->
A totally different question:  When is giving to good causes excessive?<br>
When one gives to the detriment of one's safety net--provision for emer-<br>
gencies--is one expressing faith in God's care?  Mary and the poor widow<br>
gave richly.  Jesus commended them.  When an elderly SDA lady gives away<br>
funds from her trust, trusting in the ravens, is she a paradigm of trust?<br>
How much materialism is appropriate for a Christian?<br>
<p>
Nancy<br>
