<title>Oct_1992: Micheal and Bill Gothard</title>
<h1>Micheal and Bill Gothard</h1>
Eric Snyder (<i>ESNYDER%PSUHMC.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>12 Oct 1992 07:04 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#47">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#47">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#47">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#47">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0048.html">Steven Timm: "Re:  Quick question on Colin Standish"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0046.html">Raylene: "Home-schooling"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
      Micheal is one of three angels named in the Scriptures.  He<br>
      is known as the archangel.  The Jehovah's Witnesses teach that<br>
      Jesus Christ, was once this same Micheal the archangel.  I believe<br>
      I have read somewhere that the SDA church also teaches that Jesus<br>
      and Micheal are one in the same.  The difference is that the JW's<br>
      deny the deity of Christ, while the SDA affirm it.  If necessary,<br>
      I can look up where I saw this.<br>
<p>
      To switch gears, I don't believe Bill Gothard has any children.<br>
      I don't believe he was ever married either.  Steve Timm mentioned<br>
      something about Bill's own son rebelling against him.  Did I take<br>
      something out of context ?<br>
<p>
      Eric Snyder<br>
