<title>Oct_1992: Re:  Quick question on Colin Standish</title>
<h1>Re:  Quick question on Colin Standish</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon, 12 Oct 1992 10:26:27 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#48">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#48">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#48">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#48">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0049.html">Steven Timm: "Bill Gothard"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0047.html">Eric Snyder: "Micheal and Bill Gothard"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
The book, _Defenders of the Faith_, was actually written by Drs. Colin<br>
and Russell Standish, and is commonly circulated by the Our Firm Foundation<br>
crowd, to which both are regular contributors, in fact the book was<br>
serialized in that magazine.  Raylene asked for clarification<br>
on what I had meant when I described his complaint. (Note that I <br>
don't necessarily agree with him.)<br>
<p>
The book describes in some detail the situation in Australia, where<br>
both Standishes were born and raised.  The quote from church official<br>
was "It was so easy to refuse government aid when none was offered."<br>
<p>
Then it turns briefly to the situation of SDA colleges where the financial<br>
aid is given directly to the students, to spend at the college of their choice.<br>
He points out that if a college is to receive these dollars, there are some<br>
criteria it must meet.  Unfortunately I don't remember either what these<br>
criteria are or what he claims they are.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
