With the return of Paul Gates to the net and the addition of Lenson <br>
Wong of Berkeley, we have climbed to 101 subscribers, the first time <br>
in the history of SDAnet we have been this high.  Within the past two <br>
weeks we have also added our first member from Africa  (C. Chibafa from <br>
Zimbabwe) and our first from South America (Sergio Munoz of Chile).<br>
(SDA-L has had members from S. America for quite some time.)<br>
<p>
This leaves Antarctica as the only continent where SDAnet does not have<br>
 a presence.  Any volunteers?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
