<!-- body="start" -->
Cheryl mentions that at the U of Wisconsin church organizations are permitted to<br>
use university facilities free of charge.  The same is true at Purdue Universit.<br>
<p>
Our Adventist student organization has held numerous meetings on campus.  I <br>
believe that the situation here is essentially equivalent to that which Cheryl <br>
describes, with the exception that Purdue allows political organization the <br>
same priveleges as religious ones.<br>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
