Thanks for the replies so far.  First, I will say that I have considered<br>
demon possession.  Second, I liked what Cherly had to say.  When Terry<br>
comes to church he wanders in and out of the building most of the time. <br>
He picks up a few EGW books so that he can hand them out.  He asks you<br>
whether you area Christian or a church member more than once.  He opens<br>
windows and turns off lights (fresh air is good and electricity is bad for<br>
one's health.  He talks about the "they" that is after him.  Occasionally<br>
he will be mischievious (which is what got him in trouble with someone at<br>
the business meeting).  The specific incident was his telling someone at<br>
pot luck he had AIDS and then proceeding to stick his fingers in the food.<br>
 I gather that in the past he might have been in some care facilities, but<br>
he doesn't look to favorably on the experience.  I say all of this just to<br>
give you a bit more background.  I  keep praying for some  type of good<br>
solution.<br>
<p>
Ian.<br>
