<p>
Dave,<br>
<p>
what you had to say was great. It's strange, but it seems that mathematics<br>
and science can often be useful when it comes to coping with some concepts<br>
in theology! An understanding of the scientific (or mathematical) model, and<br>
a willingness to apply it in things apart from science, seems to be very<br>
worthwhile.<br>
<p>
My ex-mathematics lecturer at Avondale College, Dr. Wilf Pinchin, had a copy<br>
of "Flatland" sitting on his desk the other week. It looked fascinating, but<br>
I didn't borrow it at the time due to a large research project which was<br>
looming over my head. It sounds like it's worth reading!<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
