<!-- body="start" -->
I too from time to time have thought about how mathematical concepts<br>
and physical laws can be used to describe God.  <br>
<p>
For those that don't know any group theory, you won't understand it,<br>
and it's not clear that even I know what I'm talking about,<br>
but could it be that in the various representations of God in the Bible,<br>
we are simply seeing different representations of the same symmetry<br>
group that describes God?<br>
<p>
For instance the "One God" of Exodus is the unitary representation,<br>
the trinity is the 3 representation, the 10 commandments are yet another,<br>
and the Shemat Yisroel  "Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy <br>
heart and all thy soul and all thy mind" yet another?<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
