<!-- body="start" -->
DaveB writes, "But frankly, I place home school, if its an option, as the top <br>
most of choices.  I have yet to find anything in EGW to contradict that, <br>
rather her strong endorsement."<br>
<p>
I recently ran across an article in a Adventist Review from the 1970's which <br>
was a transcript of a message Ellen White gave to the school board at <br>
Sanitarium, CA. I am in the process of getting a copy from a teacher friend of<br>
mine and when I do, I will post the reference. In that talk Ellen White <br>
indicated that when she made statements about keeping children out of school <br>
until they were 10 or so there were no Sabbath keeping schools in existence. <br>
She goes on to say that if there exists a Sabbath keeping school there is no <br>
reason to keep our children out of them. This article, I think, reveals the <br>
necessity of putting the statements of Ellen White into their historical <br>
context.<br>
<p>
Ed Fargusson (Compuserve 72450,2430)<br>
<p>
P.S. This is an important issue to me because I have 6 year old twin boys that<br>
started school this year.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
