<title>Oct_1992: Time for a SDAnet digest?</title>
<h1>Time for a SDAnet digest?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 15 Oct 1992 11:44:42 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#86">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#86">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#86">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#86">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0087.html">Tony: "Music for the cultured"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0085.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Home Schooling"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 From time to time people request distribution of SDAnet in a digest<br>
form.  I always say that I would do it if there was enough demand, but<br>
would prefer not to because it would be a horrible amount of work.<br>
Currently I try to send out all the messages in a group in the morning,<br>
and then once again in the evening.  It is not easy with my mail <br>
system to concatenate messages together.  It would be difficult<br>
for people to keep track of who sent what in a digest with nine messages<br>
about nine different topics, and force people who might not be interested<br>
in a particular topic to read everything to see what they want.<br>
<p>
I also point out for those who want a digest that it is possible for me <br>
to mail out the monthly archive to anyone who doesn't want to receive <br>
daily messages.  And if you would really like a digest, send me feedback<br>
and tell me so.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0087.html">Tony: "Music for the cultured"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0085.html">Dave Buxton: "Re: Home Schooling"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
