<!-- body="start" -->
Dave says, "Seventh-Day-Adventists, in their study of the Bible, find that  <br>
Michael  the Archangel  is  Jesus  the  Commander  in  chief of the heavenly <br>
host and not Himself an angel.  If you can prove from the Bible that Michael  <br>
is  a  mere angel  then  you  have  proved  that  Michael is not Jesus."<br>
<p>
That is not really true. The word "angel" in the original languages simply <br>
means "messenger." Even men and animals are called angels (although not always<br>
translated into English as angel.) Given that meaning, Jesus is the true arch <br>
messenger or archangel.<br>
<p>
Ed Fargusson (Compuserve 72450,2430)<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
