<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Dan Turk asks with regard to the proposal to set up an SDA Forum </i><br>
<i>&gt; on Compuserve, why not do it on Internet where non-compuserve subscribers</i><br>
<i>&gt; can get at it.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Two reasons:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 1)  We already have such a forum on Internet and this is it.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 2)  Those few people that subscribe to us via compuserve are taking </i><br>
<i>&gt; a per-message charge to receive the Internet-based messages of SDAnet,</i><br>
<i>&gt; as far as I understand.  (Correct me if I'm wrong.)  A compuserve</i><br>
<i>&gt; based forum would make it accessible to more people and also to</i><br>
<i>&gt; people that didn't subscribe, since Compuserve forums are open for everyone</i><br>
<i>&gt; to read (as far as I know.)</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Steve Timm</i><br>
<p>
I don't mind seeing a forum on Compuserve, but just would want to have<br>
the same dialog available (without charge) to those of us on the<br>
Internet.  That was the only reason for my comment.  I don't subscribe<br>
to Compuserve, and would thus hope I could access any such forum through<br>
the Internet.....!<br>
