To Dan Turk &amp; Net:<br>
<p>
Dan, I understand what you are saying about Internet VS CompuServe. Since<br>
I have belonged to CS since 1983 and use it regularly I would prefer a net<br>
on CS.<br>
<p>
I could be wrong but what I have understood from what some of the members<br>
have said, that internet is available to those who are working for<br>
industry or at an educational institution. My ? is for the SDAs that are<br>
in such a situation, is Internet free???<br>
<p>
ON CS I have flat membership which is $7.95 per month no matter how much<br>
you use it. The fly in the ointment for me is that I do not have a local<br>
number for CS but do use CS's 800 number which costs .15 a minute any<br>
time. In addition to that charge I pay .15 per message to receive and /or<br>
send messages through internet. CS does give us a $9.00 credit each month<br>
for messages through internet so that is a help.<br>
<p>
.......Paul<br>
