7Excerpts from mail: 19-Oct-92 Re: SDA Forum on Compuserve by McCluskey<br>
G@usl.com <br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;Why not treat Compuserve as a gateway and have it both ways?  That is,</i><br>
<i>&gt;have a single Compuserve internet address on the SDAnet mailing list</i><br>
<i>&gt;and then redistribute internally.  Ditto for outgoing mail.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt;You Compuserve wizards will have to pass judgement on whether this is</i><br>
<i>&gt;doable.</i><br>
<p>
If what Paul Gates has told us (15 cents a message in and out of <br>
Compuserve to internet) is true, this would put an incredible burden<br>
on someone's compuserve account, not to mention probably running them <br>
out of disk space in short order.  Also, such a process might be many<br>
things, but certainly not a moderated SDAnet, because messages could <br>
bounce within compuserve before moderation.<br>
<p>
We currently have two-way communication with Compuserve with all <br>
Compuserve members communicating directly with me.  Again, I ask<br>
every Compuserve subscriber of ours to E-mail me directly and tell me <br>
if a digest would be a help in handling the charges, and clear up<br>
the conflicting information we have got so far on how much it is costing <br>
you all.<br>
<p>
If a forum within Compuserve begins, I think it would be a good idea<br>
to make the echo of that group available to Internet subscribers, but<br>
it would take someone with a compuserve account willing to make the <br>
financial sacrifice to make it happen.  Of course we would offer our<br>
echo to them.  It would probably also lead me to work quickly on <br>
establishing my own subscription to CompuServe.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
