<!-- body="start" -->
Tony, I think that some on the SDANET have the idea that there is no<br>
social activity outside of the home for those students that are being home<br>
schooled. That is not the case at all here in the states. There are<br>
periodic "get togethers" with all children that are being home schooled.<br>
The YMCA has a swimming program for instance, for children that are being<br>
home schooled in the county here. In addition to this there are many<br>
educational activities planned for all who are being homeschooled state<br>
wide.<br>
<p>
I know of "clusters" of public school teachers who would not think of<br>
sending their own children to Public school. Some are in our church school<br>
(10 grades) and some are home schooled. In fact I baptized a single parent<br>
(mother) a couple of weeks ago who has been sending her child to our<br>
church school for the last couple of years.<br>
<p>
......Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
