<title>Oct_1992: Resurrection of Moses</title>
<h1>Resurrection of Moses</h1>
cheryl berthelsen (<i>cherylb@csd4.csd.uwm.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 27 Oct 92 14:51:04 -0600</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#125">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#125">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#125">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#125">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0126.html">David Plaisted: "Home Schooling"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0124.html">Russell Yonkers: "Re: Homeschool"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0128.html">Tony: "Re: Resurrection of Moses"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I have a question related to a previous discussion about whether Christ<br>
died for Enoch's sins.  My question is about the theological basis for<br>
pre-Messiah resurrection of Moses (and also relates to pre-Messiah<br>
translations of Enoch and Elijah).  What basis did God have for "claiming<br>
victory over death" by these events before victory had actually occurred?<br>
Was it because Christ could not fail in His mission?  If Christ could have<br>
failed, could Enoch, Elijah, and Moses have any "right" to be with God<br>
beforehand from Satan's perspective?  If actual victory was "guaranteed",<br>
then God had a basis for claiming Christ's victory over death before it<br>
happened but then heaven knew all along that God would win the war against<br>
evil and Satan.  From an SDA doctrinal perspective, this is difficult<br>
for me to understand.<br>
<p>
 From an LDS perspective, I can explain this.  But I was wondering if<br>
any of you had thoughts about this issue from SDA doctrine.<br>
<p>
Cheryl<br>
<p>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
          Cheryl L. Berthelsen, Ph.D., Assistant Professor<br>
              Health Information Administration Program<br>
                 School of Allied Health Professions<br>
                  University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee<br>
                  email:  cherylb@csd4.csd.uwm.edu<br>
	          phone:  (414) 229-6051<br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
