<title>Oct_1992: Home Schooling</title>
<h1>Home Schooling</h1>
David Plaisted (<i>plaisted@cs.unc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 27 Oct 92 12:24:04 -0500</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#126">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#126">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#126">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#126">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0127.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Home Schooling"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0125.html">cheryl berthelsen: "Resurrection of Moses"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
 From a (secular) area newspaper article on home schooling from<br>
Sunday October 25 1992:<br>
<p>
``If you think parents who teach their children at home are gambling on<br>
education, think again.  State figures show home-school students<br>
rank one to three years above the national average on standardized tests,<br>
including the widely used California Achievement Test (CAT). ...''<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
