        This is my first visit to SDANet. David Buxton wrote an article in the<br>
NPUC Gleaner on his hobby:computer E-mail. I wrote to him US Mail and received<br>
some interesting info re: previous forays into ferocious forums. Since he did<br>
not include SDANet in his assessment of the darker side of relgious forums, I<br>
thought I might venture myself!<br>
PERSONAL SPECS: 38 Y/O FEMALE,6'0",PROPORTIONAL WT.<br>
HOBBIES: FRIENDS,WATER AND SNOW SKIING,LEARNING,BIRDS,SCUBA,PHOTOGRAPHY,TRAVEL<br>
        I am a critical care nurse at Loma Linda University Medical Center in<br>
lovely southern California.(Smog does make beautiful sunsets - to look on the<br>
bright side) Just finished an MPH degree here and am already planning my<br>
escape back home to Oregon, to start a Nurse Practitioner Program in Portland.<br>
        I am very interested in who you all are, where you're from, and, this<br>
time, what your choice is for US Prez.come Nov.3rd. I'm leaning toward<br>
Perot,although a friend said that he is often flanked by catholic priests when<br>
he gives speeches (ominous shades of Malachi Martin!) IMHO, Bush is much too<br>
cozy with the extreme rightists.I am more comfortable with the extreme left<br>
than the right, as the lesser of two evils.I'm afraid that they'll both<br>
continue to spend money we don't have, however. BUSH:Borrow and spend.<br>
CLINTON:Tax and spend.<br>
        Waiting to hear your comments (complaints/suggestions?)<br>
