*** Reply to note of 10/28/92 07:30<br>
<p>
I saw Clinton in a town hall type meeting held in Seattle and broadcast<br>
in the Pacific Northwest.  He is the only candidate I've heard say is<br>
is strongly for the separation of Church and State.<br>
<p>
As for Perot, I read a speach he made last spring to the National Press<br>
Club in Washington DC.  It was a typical Perot speech.  The interesting<br>
comment in the speech was about the national election being on a Tuesday<br>
and how he thought it should be on a Saturday &amp; Sunday, both days "so<br>
the Seventh Day Adventists could vote too".  The only notable point of<br>
this is that of all the religous organizations he could have named, he<br>
picked SDA's.<br>
<p>
--Cam Litvin  PROFS Support  CLLITVIN<br>
