<h1>Re: Election</h1>
Daniel D Deavours (<i>ddd42961@uxa.cso.uiuc.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 28 Oct 92 11:17:37 CST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#136">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#136">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#136">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#136">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0137.html">Trevor Tompkins: "Re: more on dimensions"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0135.html">Cam Litvin: "Election"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0132.html">Steven Timm: "Election"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0138.html">Trevor Tompkins: "Re: Election"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; Sheryl voiced concern about Perot.  I attended his rally in Pittsburgh</i><br>
<i>&gt; on Sunday and saw him in person.  It seems to me that he views the</i><br>
<i>&gt; constitution almost as a roadblock; he has proposed more amendments to it</i><br>
<i>&gt; than even Bush has.  </i><br>
<p>
	Interesting.  I don't have many ways of collecting information about<br>
candidates and I haven't heard anything about that.  I do know that he has<br>
taken up the "family values" issue in a different way than Bush has.  I<br>
guess my question is what are these ammendments that he is proposing?  I<br>
really have no idea (I don't get a newspaper nor have a TV and rarely<br>
listen to the radio.)<br>
	My personal view on this is that there are two aspects.  First, we<br>
as a people are given stewardship of managing a government, so we have to<br>
excercise good judgment and vote for the candidate we think will do the best<br>
job.  Second, we have to realize that through it all, God is really in control<br>
of everything.  When the time is right, I think there will be a Sunday law<br>
passed no matter who's president.  Where the two intersect is that we should<br>
not empower a president that will make it difficult to finnish God's work<br>
and delay his coming.<br>
	If you feel this more of a political thread than a real SDA-related<br>
topic then I'd appreciate any private replies.  Thanx.<br>
<p>
Dan Deavours<br>
zeos@uiuc.edu<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
