A couple weeks ago in the Review there was a short note that the<br>
SE California Conference had failed to elect a president in a long<br>
constituency meeting, and had scheduled another meeting.  The office<br>
of president has apparently been vacant there since July.<br>
<p>
Since we have a correspondent from that office now, I'm wondering if <br>
any further information is available on this.  If memory serves, it was<br>
only a year or so ago that another stormy constituency meeting occured<br>
in that conference on the issue of the ordination of women.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
