------------<br>
<p>
Steve, you wear two hats:  you are the moderator of SDAnet, and you<br>
are an individual named Steve Timm.  While it might be true that<br>
an endorsement from the net moderator is inappropriate, the position<br>
of individual subscribers is significant.  I find it sad that you<br>
cannot distinguish who you are.  Even sadder if you think that we<br>
can't.  If you won't say for whom you are voting before the election,<br>
spare us the details afterwards.<br>
<p>
As for me, currently I'm supporting Perot.  However, because my<br>
closest advisor is pressing me to continue my former support of Bush,<br>
I am reserving my final decision until November 3.<br>
