<title>Oct_1992: Annual council:  statements on abortion, care for dying,</title>
<h1>Annual council:  statements on abortion, care for dying,</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 28 Oct 1992 21:12:34 -0500 (EST)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#141">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#141">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#141">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#141">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0142.html">Steve Hix: "Re: Homeschooling"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0140.html">Dan Blake: "Re: Election"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0144.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Annual council:  statements on abortion, care for dying,"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In this week's Review there is a short description of Annual Council<br>
actions including the voting of a statement on abortion, the first<br>
since 1971.  The text is promised by the December 31 issue.  Does anyone<br>
know how to obtain it sooner?<br>
<p>
It's also interesting to hear that R. Folkenberg (President of denomination)<br>
called for a vision of the church mission that is big enough to include<br>
member-run supporting ministries.  <br>
<p>
On one hand it is interesting because the church is breaking silence on <br>
something so important to so many people, but again it is disheartening<br>
because again we are getting into the business of deciding truth by <br>
majority vote.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
