<!-- body="start" -->
Trevor,<br>
<p>
You didn't mention fractal dimensions.  I think the complexity of fractals<br>
applies nicely to the discussion on the nature of God.  Fractal dimension<br>
basically quanifies how something changes in mass in relation to scale.<br>
The common coastline example demonstrates that the smaller the scale used<br>
to measure it, the longer the coastline gets.  Likewise with the God.  The<br>
smaller we try to make Him, the greater He becomes.<br>
<p>
cheryl<br>
