<title>Oct_1992: Thoughts on the "Right Answers"</title>
<h1>Thoughts on the "Right Answers"</h1>
Fred Christiansen (<i>fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 30 Oct 92 13:28:19 MST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#155">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#155">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#155">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#155">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0154.html">cheryl berthelsen: "Election Politics"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
A recent posting discussed struggles with those who believe they have the<br>
"Right Answers".  I am not intending this as a response to the concerns<br>
expressed in the posting but rather as brief outline of my tho'ts on<br>
certainty and personality.<br>
<p>
I do not believe God would have us wallowing in uncertainty (cf. I Th 4:13).<br>
Rather we can learn truth (John 8:32) in greater and greater measure<br>
(2 Pet 3:18) culminating in heaven, albeit not on earth (Phil 3:13).<br>
Right answers for right living are found in Scripture (2 Tim 3:16).<br>
We *can* know how He wants us to live (Ps 199:105; Is 30:21; Prov 1:23).<br>
<p>
Great men and women of God have always been people of deep conviction<br>
(e.g., check out Wylie on Luther, Knox, Farel, Hus, Jerome, Wycliffe).<br>
They have not been spiritual or "moral castrates" (to borrow a phrase from<br>
William F Buckley).  They may have withstood some people to the face<br>
but before God they were humble and teachable (Matt 11:29; James 4:6;<br>
1 Pet 5:5).  [Btw, I find it is this, above all else, that distinguishes<br>
Godly PhDs from confused ones.]  I find this attitude critical to learning<br>
(2 Pet ch 1) so that you arrive at truth (John 16:13).<br>
<p>
Without humility, no matter how right our answers may be, we instantly<br>
create resistance on the hearer's part and do damage to God's reputation<br>
and message.<br>
<pre>
-- 
Fred Christiansen, Motorola, 2900 S Diablo Way, Tempe, AZ 85282  "Canajun, eh?"
fredch@phx.mcd.mot.com  ||  uunet!phx.mcd.mot.com!fredch  ||  +1 602-438-3464
  ".. I have set before you Life and Death, blessing and cursing;  therefore
      choose Life, that both you and your children may live"  Deut 30:19
</pre>
<!-- body="end" -->
