<title>Sep_1992: Re: Vegetarians</title>
<h1>Re: Vegetarians</h1>
Tony (<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 3 Sep 1992 12:58 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#31">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#31">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#31">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#31">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0032.html">Paul Gates: "Re: temple plan"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0030.html">Tony: "Day of rest"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0009.html">Tony: "Vegetarians"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0073.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Vegetarians"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Dave,<br>
<p>
thanks for your response to my question.<br>
<p>
I have been an SDA all my life, and in my parents house we ate fish<br>
&amp; chicken occasionally, but most of the time we were vegetarian.<br>
<p>
For a while I lived in the nurses residence at a public hospital and<br>
my rent included meals at the cafeteria. This period lasted most of a year,<br>
and during this time I ate mostly whatever was served.<br>
<p>
Now I am married, and my wife is strictly vegetarian. Even if we weren't<br>
SDAs she still wouldn't eat meat. We both use eggs, dairy products and<br>
leather, and I eat some meat occasionally when I'm eating out.<br>
<p>
I would like to press you further on one phrase you used...you said<br>
you were a vegetarian for health and religious reasons. What do you mean<br>
when you say religious reasons? Do you mean to separate the two like that?<br>
Can you think of any moderate circumstances when you would eat meat?<br>
(I say moderate because I'm not after the stranded on desert island or<br>
lost at sea type circumstances!)<br>
<p>
I'm not trying to get picky with you, and I'm not about to turn around<br>
and try to rip you off over any response you might make, so please be<br>
honest - as you were with your previous answer!<br>
<p>
I get a bit edgy about the religious reasons thing, and I'm just interested<br>
to hear what you have to say.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<p>
P.S. Obviously this is an open discussion - just because I wrote "Dave"<br>
     at the beginning doesn't mean I will be upset if anyone else responds!<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
