<title>Sep_1992: Re: The minister's wife</title>
<h1>Re: The minister's wife</h1>
Paul Gates (<i>70516.420@compuserve.com</i>)<br>
<i>31 Aug 92 14:59:07 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#2">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#2">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#2">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#2">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0003.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Religious liberty on University campuses"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0001.html">Paul Gates: "Re: Andrew &amp; Omar"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
U R right Cheryl, the temple plan is not an easy thing to do. I only know<br>
of 2 churches that worked it for awhile.<br>
<p>
At present we have 4 churches particpating in our junior Academy. In mid<br>
summer I have a meeting with all perspective parents with guidlines for<br>
transportation -- church van-- etc. -- that is just for our church. Now,<br>
at the same time we include in the packet a form they can fill out<br>
requesting assistance from the church. We need a commitment from them how<br>
much they can contribute if only 10 or 20 dollars a month. I then take the<br>
requests to the church board. In 4 years we have never turned down a<br>
request! I believe this year our church portion that will be sent to the<br>
academy will be $3600.00 total -- not per month. The church believes every<br>
child should have an opportunity to go to Adventist school.<br>
<p>
The parents pay directly their portion to the school and our church<br>
treasurer does the same with the assistance. We of course alert the<br>
principal as to what the church will pay and for whom. We have members<br>
that contribute to a fund we call, "special projects." Our church also<br>
subsidizes the Academy. Our payment this year is in the neighborhood of<br>
$2000.00 a month. We live in sort of a depressed area where the main<br>
industry is "claming" and "crabing." -- Not much of an Oyster industry<br>
much any more. Some of the parents work in factories, or over at Annapolis<br>
for the state, such as secretaries, computer programmers etc. But most of<br>
the income of the members is small.<br>
<p>
.........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
