<!-- body="start" -->
Currently in SDAnet we have 94 subscribers.  73 of these I know to be SDA,<br>
some I don't know either way.   15 of these 94 are female.  Only<br>
one that I know of has claimed to be African-American.  16 are employed<br>
by church institutions, mostly Andrews and La Sierra. <br>
Our country range now includes, besides the USA, Australia, Finland,<br>
and Iceland.  It has in the past also included England and Poland. <br>
Richard Guy reads our messages from Guam through a California computer,<br>
and Danny <br>
Kumamoto reads them in Japan.  Also we have one subscriber in Hong Kong.<br>
<p>
In addition to the SDA's reading this list, we also have LDS, Worldwide<br>
Church of God, Hebrew Pentecostal, and several other religions.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
