I recall a long train ride home from Walla Walla College to Toronto<br>
by way of Chicago.  One woman in particular was very aggressively<br>
flirting with the men, sitting in whom ever's lap was empty and<br>
really carrying on the whole trip across the country.  A few hours<br>
before arrival time she put on her wedding ring and started flashing<br>
it in the faces of all those boy friends that she had collected.<br>
I happened to be right behind her getting off the train.  Her husband<br>
was there on the platform as the train slowed to a stop.  She made<br>
a flying leap into his arms from off the train and proceeded to carry<br>
on like the devoted trustable wife that she wanted him to think she was.<br>
<p>
DaveB<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
