<!-- body="start" -->
I believe I've mentioned this before, but can't let the opportunity pass.<br>
My home town in California, Ukiah (2 hours north of SF), has run a<br>
temple plan school for over 30 years.  It is a 10 grade academy, running<br>
an enrollment of around 120 in the 10 grades.  No church member pays tuition,<br>
any child of a church member is free to go at no charge.  Non-church members<br>
may enroll, but they do pay tuition.  There is a large base of support<br>
in the church, especially now that there is an Adventist hospital in town.<br>
But when I was attending there (all 10 grades) there was no SDA hospital,<br>
and the church had only 300 members or so (they have more than 600 now).<br>
It takes a LOT of commitment on the part of the members, and you can't have<br>
some remove their support just because they disagree with the teachers now<br>
and again.  But given the right combination of members and a generous dose<br>
of the Holy Spirit, the temple plan will work!<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
