Network:<br>
<p>
David Plaisted:<br>
<p>
Dave, I read your email with interest --- vegetarianism etc. -- It<br>
reminded me in times past of different things I have tried on my cereal.<br>
At present most of the time we use milk with 1% fat. But, I have tried,<br>
Apple Juice, Orange juice, Cashew milk, Home made soy milk!<br>
<p>
I too, have cut my consumption of cheese down where I eat it only<br>
occasionally. Once in a while I'll fix myself an egg sandwich but 99% of<br>
the time we use egg beaters.<br>
<p>
My reason for the vegetarian life style at this point is because I am<br>
attempting to keep my fat intake to 15 or less grams of fat a day. Also I<br>
eat so called "health foods" -- analogs -- or whatever you choose to call<br>
them, very sparingly. Fruits, fresh whenever I can get them, I really<br>
enjoy as well as steamed vegetables.<br>
<p>
........Paul<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
<ul>
