<!-- body="start" -->
Network: To Bob M.<br>
<p>
It is interesting to read some accounts of American history where it would<br>
appear to be very evident that America was more of a Christian nation<br>
then some like to admit. <br>
<p>
I am sure probably we all know on the network that originally for instance<br>
and example, there were church related, church sponsored colleges and<br>
universities. And as follows:<br>
<p>
Harvard (1636)<br>
Yale (1701)<br>
Princeton (1746)<br>
University of King's College (1789)<br>
Rutgers (1766)<br>
<p>
It was very interesting to me to discover the following statement from<br>
the charter of King's College and this was used as an advertisement in<br>
New York newspapers:<br>
<p>
"The chief thing to be arrived at in this college is to teach and engage<br>
young people to love and know God in Christ Jesus and to love and serve<br>
Him with all sobriety, godliness and richness of life, with a pure heart<br>
and willing mind."<br>
<p>
Of course higher education cannot make this statement today!<br>
<p>
&lt;&lt;Paul&gt;&gt;<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
