<!-- body="start" -->
I noticed that I posted a review of a Michael W. Smith album to SDAnet<br>
instead of to rec.music.christian.  I haven't discussed Contemporary <br>
Christian Music much here or with the youth groups I have worked with <br>
mainly because up till now it's been a non-starter.  The groups I have <br>
worked with just haven't been interested.<br>
<p>
Now it's a different ball game.  The youth in Pittsburgh have already <br>
organized themselves into an ensemble that has already played a significant<br>
role in our worship services here, and is poised to greatly expand its role.<br>
Our pastor would like a no-holds-barred celebration service, in this he <br>
is stalled by a conservative music committee, and church board.<br>
<p>
I'm planning to help them get organized, and hopefully raise whatever<br>
style of music we play to a higher performance quality.  Any suggestions<br>
from the<br>
net would be helpful, and I will share what I know over the course <br>
of the next few months.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
