<title>Sep_1992: Wedding Band</title>
<h1>Wedding Band</h1>
Lisa Parry (<i>parry@gandalf.cs.andrews.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 3 Sep 92 9:50:54 EDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#43">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#43">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#43">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#43">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0044.html">Ben Clausen: "Re: Address for Biblical Research Inst."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0042.html">Steven Timm: "Music ideas"</a>
<li> <b>In reply to:</b> <a href="0015.html">Scott Mattes: "Sat v. Sun Sabbath"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0050.html">Bill Nickless: "Wedding Band"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Since jewelry/wedding band is under discussion right now, I'm curious on the<br>
net reaction to a story I heard yesterday (true story, friend of mine <br>
experienced it).<br>
<p>
A young mother works for the bookstore on the SDA university campus.  She does <br>
not wear a wedding band by her own choice.  She is happily married with a 6 <br>
month old child.  The manager of the store asked her to wear a wedding band.<br>
He cites the reason that there are many single university students coming <br>
through the store, and it's nicer for them to know from the beginning who was<br>
single and who wasn't!!!  She actually thinks the reason is that she looks very<br>
young and has a small child, and he doesn't was it to look bad (like she's a <br>
young single mother).<br>
<p>
I've heard plenty of stories where people were asked to take wedding bands off<br>
my SDA administrators, but I've never heard one where they were asked to wear <br>
them!<br>
<p>
What do you think??<br>
<p>
<pre>
-- 
"If God is for us, who can be against us?"            Lisa Parry
--Romans 8:31, last sentence                   parry@andrews.edu
</pre>
