<!-- body="start" -->
The standard answer to Bill Oblitey's question is that animals eat<br>
plants, so if you eat animals you cause more suffering to plants than<br>
if you eat plants.  But, I don't believe plants have any sense of pain,<br>
or very little.  God gave Adam the plants to eat, and the creation<br>
was very good at the beginning (Genesis 1 - 3).<br>
<p>
	Dave Plaisted<br>
<p>
[However, note that it was only after sin that "the herb of the field"<br>
was added to the fruits of the trees of the garden as part of Adam's<br>
diet.  So the diet went from things which did not necessarily involve<br>
killing the plant to things which did.  Not that plants can feel <br>
the pain, anyway.   SCT]<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
