One more thing to add:<br>
<p>
The single students, such as myself, also face their own hurdles.  Many are <br>
hesitant to commit much time to activities at the university-town church <br>
(which they may or may not have transferred their membership to) since they <br>
have social interests at another church or are seeking to form friendships<br>
at other SDA churches.  While I lived in the San Francisco Bay area, I <br>
enjoyed visiting other SDA churches and meeting new people.  I have been<br>
less able to do this since I have been a Sabbath School teacher.  Taking<br>
responsibilities at the local church necessarily curtails your travel.<br>
<p>
<p>
Tim Swensen<br>
