<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; [However, note that it was only after sin that "the herb of the field"</i><br>
<i>&gt; was added to the fruits of the trees of the garden as part of Adam's</i><br>
<i>&gt; diet.</i><br>
<p>
But prior to the fall, every green herb was given as food to<br>
everything that creepeth upon the earth, wherein there is life<br>
(Gen.1:30).  Green herbs being meet for food was not part of<br>
God's curse for sin.<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt; So the diet went from things which did not necessarily involve</i><br>
<i>&gt; killing the plant to things which did.</i><br>
<p>
This is ridiculous.  You cannot kill something that does not<br>
have life.  Read Genesis 1 &amp; 2.  The biblical concept of life<br>
does not include plants.  (Almost wrote plant life :^).<br>
<p>
Dan Blake<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
