<title>Sep_1992: A record week</title>
<h1>A record week</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Mon,  7 Sep 1992 11:28:36 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#81">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#81">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#81">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#81">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Steven Timm: "New Greater SDA-L Directory"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0080.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "God's Law - Moses's Law"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
In the first 7 days of September we processed 83 messages through SDAnet.<br>
This is, as far as I know, a record for any given week.  The problem is <br>
that many of these messages have bounced back at me because people's machines<br>
have been down.  Tracking down down machines and sorting through all the <br>
bouncing messages is the biggest hassle of moderating SDAnet.  You folks<br>
can help by letting me know in advance when you are going to lose an <br>
account or when your machine is going to be down for an extended <br>
period of time.  <br>
<p>
If we continue at this pace for the rest of the month, we will set an all-<br>
time record for SDAnet traffic.  Let's keep it going.<br>
<p>
Steve<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
