<title>Sep_1992: SDA-L:  Let the personals begin</title>
<h1>SDA-L:  Let the personals begin</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+%ANDREW.CMU.EDU%CMU.EDU@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>07 Sep 1992 14:59:38 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#83">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#83">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#83">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#83">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0084.html">Steven Timm: "SDA-L:  New policy on forwarding"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0082.html">Steven Timm: "New Greater SDA-L Directory"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0137.html">Lisa Parry: "SDA-L:  Hmmm, think people are shy..."</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
SDA-L specifically is for exchange between SDA students and faculty on<br>
college campuses (as opposed to the more doctrinally oriented list SDAnet<br>
which I moderate.)  With that goal I propose a thread of biographies where<br>
we share about each other, and possibly also the type of people we might<br>
like to meet.  I follow with my own (though obviously most people know<br>
about me<br>
already)<br>
<p>
My name is Steve Timm, I'm 26 years old, white, male, and single. I was<br>
raised in the SDA church, born and raised in the metro area of Grand<br>
Rapids, MI.  I attended Cedar Lake Academy and Andrews University,<br>
graduating from there with BA in Physics and MS in Computer Science.<br>
I've been a graduate<br>
student at Carnegie Mellon in physics for four years now, going into the<br>
fifth.  I have about a year left to finish my Ph.D.  I spoke about<br>
Illinois a lot because I was living at Fermilab for the last two years.<br>
Now I am physically in Pittsburgh, the same town as my computers.<br>
<p>
Most of my fun revolves around helping young people.  This has led<br>
recently to puppet ministry, drama, being in several music groups,<br>
playing the organ and guitar.  We have the makings of a great band here<br>
in Pittsburgh and I<br>
have just begun to work with them.<br>
<p>
Types of people I would like to meet<br>
1)  Anyone with a job offer in physics.<br>
2)  Good speakers or artists that communicate well to youth.<br>
3)  Single females with a desire to travel and no objection to being poor.<br>
<p>
All right:  I've bared my soul to the net, now it's your turn.<br>
There are people who have been subscribed to the net since the beginning,<br>
and I don't even know their names.  Let's speak out.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
