<title>Sep_1992: RE: renting churches</title>
<h1>RE: renting churches</h1>
Cam Litvin (<i>CLLITVIN@bluemoon.profs.tek.com</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 9 Sep 92 15:59:39 PDT</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#112">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#112">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#112">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#112">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0113.html">Tony: "Re: Sabbath issues"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0111.html">Stan Macasieb: "re: Renting Churches"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt;Does anyone have some insight on renting practices of an SDA church to</i><br>
<i>&gt;Sunday keeping church?  I understand there may be some view points on</i><br>
<i>&gt;both sides, those for and against it.  I realize the identity of the chrch</i><br>
<i>&gt;may be an issue but if it is considered not to be of "radical" theologyand</i><br>
<i>&gt;temperament, should we rent to a Sunday keeping church?  Would it be</i><br>
<i>&gt;promoting Sunday worship?</i><br>
<p>
<i>&gt;(This is to be debated at the next church board meeting and wonder what</i><br>
<i>&gt;the debate is all about.)</i><br>
<p>
Hi Alice,<br>
<p>
   The two churches I have attended the last 30 years have periodically<br>
rented their facilities to a "Sunday Keeping Church".  The conference<br>
posisiton is that each church may chose to do what they want to do.<br>
<p>
   I think there are several things to consider.  1.  Have a unbiased<br>
church business meeting and give your members an opportunity to hear<br>
the advanatages and disadvantages.  It is important that the church<br>
family is united in the proposal.  2.  If the church members chose to<br>
rent the church, create a list of guidelines such as rent amount,<br>
cleaning, what rooms are used, etc for the renter to agree too before<br>
the church is rented.<br>
<p>
   I have seen a church divided because the board approved the renting<br>
of a facility to a organization, then try to get the church to approve<br>
their action after the fact.  I have also seen another situation that<br>
followed some guidelines which has worked well for the both churches.<br>
<p>
Regards,<br>
Cam Litvin  Cameron.L.Litvin@TEK.COM<br>
<p>
--Cam Litvin  PROFS Support  CLLITVIN<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
