<title>Sep_1992: Epistle to the Magnesians</title>
<h1>Epistle to the Magnesians</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Thu, 10 Sep 1992 20:59:55 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#122">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#122">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#122">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#122">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0123.html">Ian Brown: "searching for the truth"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0121.html">Steven Timm: "Re: Bible to interpret itself"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0132.html">Nancy Vyhmeister: "Re: Epistle to the Magnesians"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Scott raised an issue with the Epistle to the Magnesians,<br>
claiming it was both earlier and more Sunday-keeping than <br>
I had ever heard of before.  Somebody posted on it, but<br>
I don't think they answered Scott's point.  <br>
Does someone have Bacchiocchi's book _From Sabbath To Sunday?_<br>
This reference is certainly covered there, but I don't have <br>
one handy.  Help on this reference would be much appreciated.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
