<title>Sep_1992: Re: Sabbath</title>
<h1>Re: Sabbath</h1>
Tony (<i>PHTH1@cc.newcastle.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Fri, 11 Sep 1992 11:48 +1000</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#127">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#127">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#127">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#127">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0128.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re: Translation Faith"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0126.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Re:  God's Law portrays His character?"</a>
<li> <b>Maybe in reply to:</b> <a href="0172.html">Danny Kumamoto: "Sabbath"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0177.html">Tony: "Re: Sabbath"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Nancy,<br>
<p>
the way you approach the Sabbath is very constructive, and in my opinion<br>
the Sabbath is important for all the reasons you listed. Jesus makes those<br>
points well with the Sabbath miracles and so on.<br>
<p>
You go on to say that the "holy time is not transferable". This must lead<br>
you to be very concerned about whether or not you are observing the correct<br>
24-hour period.<br>
<p>
I myself am not so sure about the holy time thing. Consider the case of<br>
the date-line thing in Tonga. Now that the weekday names have been changed,<br>
normal Sunday-keeping churches worship on the same day as SDAs. Would you<br>
consider that the benefits of Sabbath would now be available to Sunday-<br>
keepers whereas before they weren't? I know many people who worship on<br>
Sunday don't observe a Sabbath then the way we do, but treat that <br>
separately for now.<br>
<p>
Personally, I would *like* to think that God is able to bless us anyway,<br>
depending mainly on our own attitude to him, to worship and to life. I am<br>
not convinced that this *is* the case, but I'd like to think it is.<br>
<p>
Perhaps a good experiment would be to have groups of people keeping Friday,<br>
Saturday and Sunday. Making the assumption that one of these days is blessed<br>
more than the others, we would only need to develop a spiritual meter rule<br>
and we could discover which one it is. ;)<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
