Hi all<br>
<p>
<p>
Steve writes :<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; It seems like there may be a nice little offshoot growing up here in </i><br>
<p>
Well I know absolutely nothing about what you speak about, so my comments<br>
are unbiased.<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt; "Will the generation that is</i><br>
<i>&gt; translated to heaven without seeing death at the end of time have a</i><br>
<i>&gt; character any different than those who have died in Christ over the</i><br>
<i>&gt; years?"</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<p>
Well they sure have to if they are going to go through the close of probation<br>
without a mediator in the heavenly sanctuary.<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; Things that would seem to indicate NO:</i><br>
<i>&gt; 1) No transformation of character is made at the Second Coming (or is it)</i><br>
<p>
thats right because that change has to happen in our lives now. <br>
Why do you think the Lord has been delaying his comming ? <br>
Could it be because we are not ready to meet Him ?<br>
<p>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Things that would seem to indicate YES:</i><br>
<i>&gt; 1)  Those in the Bible that were translated (Enoch, Elijah, Jesus)</i><br>
<i>&gt; were extraordinary men of God.</i><br>
<i>&gt; 2)  Ellen White's statements about God waiting for His character to </i><br>
<i>&gt; be reproduced in His people before He comes.</i><br>
<p>
Shouldn't this be enough evidence ?<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt; 3)  The experimental fact that no one is persecuting us right now</i><br>
<i>&gt; because we're not doing anything to deserve it.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; I think most of us would agree that in Christ, freedom from sin is </i><br>
<i>&gt; possible.  The question is, is it necessary?</i><br>
<p>
Christ came to save us from SIN. MAtt 1:21<br>
have we really been saved unless we have been saved from sin ?<br>
Are you asking whether salvation from sin is necessary ?<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
