<title>Sep_1992: SDA-L:  Are people shy?</title>
<h1>SDA-L:  Are people shy?</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+%ANDREW.CMU.EDU%CMU.EDU@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>11 Sep 1992 08:37:53 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#138">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#138">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#138">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#138">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0139.html">Blessed Ballesteros: "SDA-L:  Are people shy?"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0137.html">Lisa Parry: "SDA-L:  Hmmm, think people are shy..."</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Lisa Parry thinks people may be shy.  I can think of two other<br>
reasons that we might not be seeing responses on this thread.<br>
<p>
1)  People are too busy, lazy, or apathetic to respond.<br>
<p>
2)  People are trying to respond to the messages that are tagged SDA-L<br>
and they are bouncing back.<br>
<p>
For the latter, unless you have signed on to SDA-L by sending a message<br>
directly to LISTSERV@LLUVM.Bitnet saying SUB SDA-L YOURNAME<br>
you can't respond directly to those messages.  (Once you do, you will<br>
get double copies of all SDA-L messages until you SET SDA-L NOMAIL).<br>
<p>
What you should do, if you're not subscribed, is send your response to<br>
these threads to me, with SDA-L in the subject line, I will forward it.<br>
<p>
But I think Lisa is right.  There are some 30 people who have never<br>
posted a thing from the time they signed on to SDAnet or SDA-L.  We need<br>
to create an environment where they feel free to post.<br>
<p>
Ideas are welcome.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
