<title>Sep_1992: SDA-L biography of Ian Brown</title>
<h1>SDA-L biography of Ian Brown</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+%ANDREW.CMU.EDU%CMU.EDU@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>11 Sep 1992 08:29:36 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#140">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#140">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#140">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#140">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0141.html">Lola: "renting churches"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0139.html">Blessed Ballesteros: "SDA-L:  Are people shy?"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
My name is Ian Robertson Brown, I go by the computer name of Malachi<br>
Robertson as someone already was using 'Ian Brown' as a login name.<br>
<p>
I am currently a student at the University of Iowa.  I am planning to<br>
graduate next spring with a B.S. in economics.  After that I hope to go to<br>
Andrews and study religion (quite a change from economics!  You should<br>
have seen the blank stare on my advisors face when I told him I might go<br>
to seminary.).<br>
<p>
I became a Seventh-day Adventist after a series of meetings conducted by<br>
Amazing Facts here at the university.  I have been a church member since<br>
1989.  Before that I was a believer in a god, but no specific religious<br>
persuasion.  I am currently working with my fellow church members to start<br>
a campus organization.<br>
<p>
My hobbies include reading, interacting on the computer, and ocassionally<br>
playing the piano.<br>
<p>
I am 21 and lived 18 of those years in Houston, Texas.  I moved to Iowa<br>
for the climate and for the good economics program.  I also have relatives<br>
near by which doesn't hurt.  I am a single guy living with two married<br>
couples in a large apartment in Coralville, Iowa, which is right next door<br>
to Iowa City and the university.<br>
<p>
I will add that I am glad to be a follower of our Lord Jesus Christ, and a<br>
member of the group of followers to whom he has given much truth.  May we<br>
gladly serve him by teaching the truth to others and by continually searching<br>
for more.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
