<title>Sep_1992: renting churches</title>
<h1>renting churches</h1>
Lola (<i>AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>14 Sep 1992 12:31:12 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#141">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#141">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#141">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#141">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0142.html">Steven Timm: "Listening session with Columbia Union officers"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0140.html">Steven Timm: "SDA-L biography of Ian Brown"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
I've been on both sides of the renting church issue, meaning I've been<br>
 in a congregation where we rented our building to another denomination<br>
on Sunday, and I've experienced having to rent another church for our<br>
services on Sabbath.<br>
<p>
Cheryl's comments about hammering all the details out ahead of time are<br>
very apt.  When we rented for Sabbath we were sometimes turned out with<br>
only a week's notice because there was going to be a wedding.  Or there<br>
would be kids running in and out of the building because the other<br>
church had a youth trip and they were meeting in the parking lot before<br>
leaving.  That kind of thing can be terribly disturbing to your service.<br>
<p>
As for renting the SDA building, I never had any qualms about it.  I<br>
viewed it as helping out another group of Christian brothers and sisters.<br>
And because I was on the committee to find a place to rent for ourselves,<br>
I know how difficult it can be to find a church that is willing to<br>
share space!  Plus, the income did wonderful things for our budget, even<br>
though we charged barely over what it cost us to keep the utilities on<br>
for the extra days per month.<br>
<p>
The cleaning issue was always the most troublesome.  As SDAs we didn't<br>
want to have our janitor clean after church on Sabbath for the Sunday<br>
group, nor did we want any of them coming in Sabbath afternoon to clean.<br>
That left Saturday night or Sunday morning early.  We finally solved it<br>
by agreeing to pick up as much as possible after church on Sabbath<br>
without actually cleaning, and the Sunday people would just not fuss if<br>
there was stuff on the carpet or a fingerprint or two on the woodwork.<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
