When I asked people to post biographies, it was not my major intention to<br>
turn SDA-L into a dating service.  Married people as well as single<br>
should post biographies.  You notice on my list of priorities meeting<br>
young women was third, after finding a job and something else.<br>
Being acquainted with the demographics of the list as I am, I think it<br>
rather unlikely that anyone will ever answer such a personal ad, and I<br>
don't expect people to.<br>
<p>
So, everyone, please speak up.  Especially you 30 or so SDAnet people<br>
that have never posted a thing since you got on.<br>
<p>
If you got a double copy of Tony's message, BTW, that's my fault.<br>
Nothing wrong with the net.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
