<title>Sep_1992: Summary of listening session</title>
<h1>Summary of listening session</h1>
Steven Timm (<i>st0o+@andrew.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>Tue, 15 Sep 1992 09:17:17 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#147">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#147">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#147">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#147">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0148.html">BRENDA GRIMES: "LET ME OFF THIS LIST"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0146.html">Steven Timm: "SDA-L:  Re:  What makes a biography interesting"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
<li> <b>Next in thread:</b> <a href="0151.html">Lisa Parry: "SDA-L response"</a>
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Some of the things that we agreed we were pleased with in the church:<br>
<p>
1)  That the church was listening to young adults, as evidenced by the session.<br>
<p>
2)  That we have the right message for the time.<br>
<p>
3)  That we are beginning to realize what it means to be involved in our<br>
community.<br>
<p>
4)  The wide range of educational opportunities that are available<br>
<p>
Some of the troubles that our group of young adults agreed were the major <br>
problems in the church to us:<br>
<p>
1)  Diluting our message to blend in with the world.<br>
<p>
2)  The education gap between college-educated and not, and the difficulty<br>
of constructing a church to appeal to both.<br>
<p>
3)  The problem of separate conferences for blacks and whites above<br>
the local church level.<br>
<p>
4)  The lack of support for Christian education <br>
<p>
5)  The lack of programming geared to the 25-40 age group.<br>
<p>
  6)  A difficulty in distinguishing what is moral from what is cultural.<br>
<p>
7)  A crisis in spiritual authority.<br>
<p>
8)  A power gap between those who feel they 'own' the church and the <br>
younger generations<br>
<p>
Some of the visions we came up with to change this<br>
<p>
1)  Improve quality of church's educational system<br>
<p>
2)  Develop a union-wide support group for young adults, with a recognized<br>
leader in each church, who should serve on church board.<br>
<p>
3)  Build our own establishment structure by volunteering in areas<br>
otherwise neglected or inventing new offices in which to work.  <br>
<p>
4)  Build trust between the generations by giving of ourselves.<br>
<p>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
