<!-- body="start" -->
It seems that Jeff Tosk may really have raised a concern.  SDA-L<br>
members are voting with their subscriptions, and there has been a major<br>
number of signoffs from SDA-L in the last week.  Biographies have always<br>
been part of SDA-L's meager traffic.  I thought that adding the type of<br>
people one wants to meet would be a natural extension.  Perhaps I was wrong.<br>
<p>
Also, perhaps I am overreacting.  Whenever SDA-L generates a spurt of<br>
traffic we have signoffs.  I realize there are some people out there who<br>
would like to see SDA-L remain a low traffic list and just can't handle<br>
the 100 posts a month of SDAnet.  I also realize there are some people on<br>
SDA-L who would just as soon I drop dead.  Please, if the volume of traffic<br>
or the nature of the topics is really a problem, let us know by mail<br>
rather than with a desubscription.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
