<p>
To the initial point, I don't recall whether Steve suggested that this<br>
let's-get-to-know-each-other period was specifically meant for<br>
singles only. I didn't save that first post, but I think you should<br>
quote first before flaming. Nonetheless, I feel that Steve means well<br>
and maybe, not on an obvious level, we can get to know each other<br>
personally through this forum, singles and married folk.<br>
<p>
This issue is also related to an issue encountered in the usenet group<br>
soc.culture.filipino, as well as other cultural newsgroups.<br>
<p>
 From time to time someone will post a singles ad or some kind of program<br>
to get to know eligible Filipinos or Filipinas back home. The idea of<br>
posting that type of garbage on a cultural newsgroup smacks<br>
of colonialism, that the "strong, white male" gets his pick of those<br>
"obedient, young geisha-girl-types."<br>
<p>
OK, off my pulpit. Sorry. Let me crawl back to my lab bench.<br>
<p>
