<!-- body="start" -->
Hello, world! This is Stanleyned Guiloreza Macasieb here. Stan, for short.<br>
<p>
I occasionally pop in and out of SDAnet conversation since I logged<br>
in back in May 1992.<br>
<p>
I'm closing in on my 25th birthday in December. I was born and raised<br>
in Chicago to Filipino immigrants. I graduated from Lane Tech HS in<br>
Chicago in 1986 and the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign in<br>
1989 with a bachelor's in electrical engineering. Believe it or not,<br>
I actually do some useful work here at Motorola in northwest suburban<br>
Schaumburg as a hardware design engineer.<br>
<p>
I have two younger brothers, still live at home with my folks to<br>
save some moolah for a place of my own, am currently not seeing<br>
any girl in particular (nudge, nudge, wink, wink!). Hobbies include<br>
my computer, basketball, volleyball, and rollerblading. I also am<br>
an audio/visual freak, so I own a sizeable collection of CDs and cassettes,<br>
and I also own a Radio Shack DX-440 shortwave whenever I feel like<br>
listening in on the world.<br>
<p>
I first became involved in the church as a 6th grader in the Pathfinders<br>
program. I was baptized in May 1982 and had stayed involved with<br>
the church at a low level until January 1991 when I became a Sabbath<br>
School leader and a member of the Twentysomething fellowship group<br>
in the Chicago area. I have now added the title of Communications<br>
Secretary at the local church to my resume since July 1992.<br>
<p>
Whew! That covers it. So who's next???<br>
<p>
******************************************************************************<br>
--Stan Macasieb (stanm@comm.mot.com)              |<br>
--Motorola, Land Mobile Products Sector           |<br>
--Schaumburg, IL (just another suburb of Chicago) |<br>
