<!-- body="start" -->
<i>&gt; I have the book on order and should get it in a few days.  However, I</i><br>
<i>&gt; am a terribly slow reader, and _1994_ is a sizable book (&gt;500 pages).</i><br>
<i>&gt; If you want timely and varied feedback, I suggest several mature</i><br>
<i>&gt; Christians read it.  Don't worry about making Mr. Camping rich.  He</i><br>
<i>&gt; does not claim any special revalation from God.  He bases his</i><br>
<i>&gt; conclusion on a careful exegesis of the Bible.  He goes (I believe)</i><br>
<i>&gt; rather heavily into numerology.</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; Resist the impulse to slam him.  I have no doubt that he is a true</i><br>
<i>&gt; believer.  His defense of the Bible as the word of God is powerful.</i><br>
<i>&gt; He did not want to write this book.  He did not want to draw such</i><br>
<i>&gt; attention to his ministry.  But believing as he did, he was compelled;</i><br>
<i>&gt; wouldn't you be?  The worst you could say is that he is deluded, and</i><br>
<i>&gt; you shouldn't say that until you have read the book, hence, my order.</i><br>
<i>&gt; On the other side of the coin, if he is right, he has an urgent</i><br>
<i>&gt; message to proclaim, one to be sure that is already written:</i><br>
<i>&gt; </i><br>
<i>&gt; 2 Corinthians chapter 6</i><br>
<i>&gt;   1 We then, as workers together with him, beseech you also that</i><br>
<i>&gt; ye receive not the grace of God in vain.</i><br>
<i>&gt;   2 (For he saith, I have heard thee in a time accepted, and in</i><br>
<i>&gt; the day of salvation have I succoured thee: behold, now is the</i><br>
<i>&gt; accepted time; behold, now is the day of salvation.)</i><br>
<p>
I have a friend who bought into some analysis done by a dentist at<br>
LLU.  He tried to show that a certain year (1992 I think) was the<br>
"jubilee of jubilees" and therefore the year when the world would end.<br>
<p>
Unless you are mathematically sophisticated this kind of stuff can be<br>
very convincing while also being false.  Martin Gardner, the famous<br>
mathematical games writer, once showed how the Pope could be linked<br>
with 666, and then went on to show how the name "Ellen G. White" could<br>
just as easily be linked.  His point was that you can play all sorts<br>
of games with numbers.<br>
<p>
Glen McCluskey<br>
glenm@usl.com<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
