<title>Sep_1992: SDA-L:  Tony's bio</title>
<h1>SDA-L:  Tony's bio</h1>
Anthony Dyson (<i>st0o+%ANDREW.CMU.EDU%CMU.EDU@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>16 Sep 1992 21:02:23 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#160">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#160">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#160">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#160">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0161.html">Cam Litvin: "Another Bio..."</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0159.html">McCluskey G: "Re: 1994"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Well, here goes. (This could be a mistake - I kind of like the anonymity<br>
of long distance e-mail!)<br>
<p>
Name:    Anthony John Dyson<br>
DOB:     27th January, 1968<br>
<p>
Only people who don't know me call me Anthony, because I'm always<br>
introduced as Tony. That way I can always tell who has read my name<br>
somewhere and who my real friends are. :)<br>
<p>
I've been a white male SDA all my life, and in January 1990 I became a<br>
married white male SDA. My father is a minister, and in the South Pacific<br>
Division that means I don't have a home town. I was born in Tasmania, and<br>
lived in New Zealand and PNG as well as the Aussie mainland during my<br>
school years.<br>
<p>
I attended the SDA tertiary institution in Australia, Avondale College, where<br>
I obtained a B.Ed.(Physics). Following that, I taught there for a year (!),<br>
picking up some work left by people on study leave. Currently I am studying<br>
at the University of Newcastle, doing the fourth year of B.Sc.(Hons), still<br>
majoring in physics. My future plans are totally indeterminate until I find<br>
out my results at the end of the year!<br>
<p>
One of the best things I ever did was to take two years off study in between<br>
high school and college. Part of that time I spent as a salesman in a large<br>
discount store, and the rest as an assistant nurse in the psychiatric ward<br>
of a North Queensland hospital. During that time I realized how much there is<br>
to life that I know nothing about!<br>
<p>
As far as interests go, I enjoy music (listening, performing and producing),<br>
basketball, computing and lots of other things. Unfortunately my hobbies have<br>
taken somewhat of a back seat this year, because I'm chasing a scholarship<br>
so that I can continue with my study program. I'll probably find out in a<br>
couple of months that they didn't take enough of a back seat, but not to<br>
worry...<br>
<p>
So there's a few paragraphs which only go to show how many words you can<br>
write without really saying anything significant about yourself! I would<br>
introduce my wife, but she's just signed onto the net herself, and I'll<br>
let her make her own introductions.<br>
<p>
Tony<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
<p>
