<title>Sep_1992: bios</title>
<h1>bios</h1>
Lola (<i>AAGAARD%morekypr.BITNET@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>20 Sep 1992 10:54:24 -0400 (EDT)</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#167">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#167">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#167">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#167">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0168.html">C. Allen Roy: "sda-l Ark-athon II"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0166.html">Jeff Tosk: "SDA-L: Re: Taste and see"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Two biographies in one here.<br>
   I'm Lola Aagaard (Boram) -- keeping my maiden name professionally<br>
has resulted in a certain amount of schizoid behavior.  I married<br>
Robert Boram in 1981 and I'll give you his bio too.<br>
<p>
I am fifth generation SDA on one side of my family and fourth on the<br>
other.  My mom was raised in the mission field (Malaysia) and two of<br>
my siblings have been missionaries.  My eldest brother teaches at<br>
Pacific Union College and my sister teaches at Mountain View Academy<br>
in California.  I tell you that to show how steeped in Adventism our<br>
family is ... and yet Robert and I turned down the opportunity to work<br>
at Andrews.  What is this generation coming to?<br>
<p>
Anyway, I am a double graduate of PUC (nursing and Biology) and also<br>
a double graduate of the University of Oklahoma (MPH and then PHD).<br>
I'm in my eighth month of pregnancy with our first child, so am not<br>
working full-time at this point.  When I do teach, it is generally to\<br>
graduate students in education:  research methods, statistics, computer<br>
data analysis, measurement, even adult education theory.  Beginning<br>
October 1, I will be a half-time research associate with Appalachia<br>
Educational Laboratory, which means I get to work at home most of the<br>
time and travel about 3 days a month to collect data.<br>
<p>
HHobbies?  Who really has time for hobbies?  We just bought an old<br>
house on about 2 acres and I'm discovering the "joys" of being a<br>
home-owner.  Previously I used to do a lot of singing in community<br>
choirs and a bit of paid solo work for various churches, but that<br>
is slacking off as I get busier (not to mention more out of breath as<br>
my belly increases in size!).  My main hobby now is trying to figure out<br>
a cheap but non-violent way to keep the groundhogs out of my garden!<br>
<p>
Now for Robert.  He also is third and fourth generation SDA, grew up in<br>
the mission field (Nigeria and Sierra Leone).  He is a graduate of La<br>
Sierra (Biophysics) and a double grad of Univ. of OK (MS in Physics,<br>
PHD in Science Education).  He is an assistant professor in Science<br>
Education at Morehead State University, Morehead, KY.  He's really<br>
excited about the coming child, but less excited about all the home<br>
repairs he's having to do!  Hobbies: weather-watching, stained glass<br>
making.<br>
<p>
We're both active in the little church here (membership=44, attending=20<br>
on a good day).  Robert has Juniors, I am one of the adult S.S. teachers<br>
and superintendents.  I also play the piano once a month, and am<br>
supposed to be putting out a bulletin, but can't locate the covers!<br>
<p>
Hope this goes through -- it's the second time I've tried.<br>
<p>
Lola<br>
Aagaard@Morekypr<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
