<title>Sep_1992: SDA-L: A Bio from Finland</title>
<h1>SDA-L: A Bio from Finland</h1>
Minna (<i>st0o+%ANDREW.CMU.EDU%CMU.EDU@bitnet.cc.cmu.edu</i>)<br>
<i>21 Sep 1992 09:12:12 -0400</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#170">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#170">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#170">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#170">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0171.html">Steven Timm: "Making the church safe for the Geritol set"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0169.html">Scott Mattes: "Meaning of Dispensations"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
My name is Minna Kristiina Puustelli.  I'm a 21-year-old female student and I<br>
study linguistics (English and German) at the University of Jyv{skyl{ in<br>
Finland.  In about 3 years I should finish my studies and start teaching<br>
English as a foreign language. In addition to English and German I've tried<br>
to learn some Swedish (the other official language of Finland), French and<br>
Russian - and there are so many other languages that I would be interested in!<br>
Hobbies... I don't have many of them. I play the piano, I go swimming once in<br>
a while... that's about it at the moment.<br>
<p>
I'm an SDA.  I was baptized only a year ago and I'm really glad that I made<br>
the decision to follow Jesus.  Even though it means struggling every day, it's<br>
worth it. I'm sure you all would agree. My mother is adventist, but my father<br>
and my brother (19) are not. We have adventist schools in Finland but I<br>
haven't atteded them. I've been to Newbold College in England for one<br>
year and also to Bogenhofen in Austria for a summer course so I know<br>
what adventist<br>
schools are like.<br>
<p>
I enjoy reading the discussions on the net. I have to confess that my Bible-<br>
knowledge is not very wide and, therefore, I can't comment on many of the<br>
topics, but on the other hand it makes it more interesting for me to read<br>
your 'debates' and seek the answers from the Bible myself. I find the bios<br>
fascinating - hopefully there are more of them coming!<br>
<p>
                                Your sister in Jesus Christ<br>
                                Minna<br>
<p>
                                mkp@jyu.fi<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
