<!-- body="start" -->
Since our young adults discussion group last week voted that we should<br>
improve the quality of our educational system from top to bottom, <br>
I am doing my part.  Our local church school has an Apple //e computer,<br>
and I have just got it back up and working over the weekend.  If there <br>
is any public domain software that you know about, especially for <br>
math and science, please let me know.  <br>
<p>
This is part of a new program our church is doing this year, trying to<br>
involve our many local professionals in supporting and enhancing the <br>
church school program.  A little bit of help can go a long way.<br>
Unless I hear from a lot of other people saying to share these ideas,<br>
responses should just come as E-mail to me.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
