<!-- body="start" -->
Steve,<br>
<p>
Doesn't the verses about faith without works is dead answer some of your<br>
perplexity about the Christian life and what we do after we have<br>
justification by faith?  Justification by faith is not justification for<br>
me to be idle, but it is the call for us to serve our Lord.  Remember the<br>
judgment will be one of works.  We must ask ourselves if we have allowed<br>
God to hang some fruit on us the branch?  Or have we said it is nice to be<br>
a branch, but don't hang nothing on me?  When one looks to the "faith"<br>
chapter of Hebrews one ought to notice that each of the people outlined<br>
preformed some action.  The action demonstrated their faith as being true.<br>
I little about this issue of whether the last generation will be somehow<br>
without sin and able to do no wrong, but I do know that we must say not I,<br>
but Christ and allow him to do in our lives the work he was able to do in<br>
his own.<br>
<p>
Ian.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
