<!-- body="start" -->
On the netnews board soc.religion.christian there has been quite<br>
an active discussion going on regarding the claim of one scholar<br>
that two fragments of papyrus found at Qumran bear parts of the New Testament,<br>
thus dating it before Qumran was taken over by the Romans in the AD 60's.<br>
But these are very small fragments and it's hard to tell for sure.<br>
Many scholars are adamantly opposed to this view.<br>
<p>
Steve Timm<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
