<title>Sep_1992: Did NT Apostles worry about attaing perfection?</title>
<h1>Did NT Apostles worry about attaing perfection?</h1>
Ruben Gonzalez (<i>ruben@ee.uts.edu.au</i>)<br>
<i>Wed, 30 Sep 92 14:25:26 EST</i>
<p>
<ul>
<li> <b>Messages sorted by:</b> <a href="date.html#208">[ date ]</a><a href="index.html#208">[ thread ]</a><a href="subject.html#208">[ subject ]</a><a href="author.html#208">[ author ]</a>
<!-- next="start" -->
<li> <b>Next message:</b> <a href="0209.html">Tony: "Broadening our mission"</a>
<li> <b>Previous message:</b> <a href="0207.html">Ruben Gonzalez: "Translation Faith - 2 standards"</a>
<!-- nextthread="start" -->
</ul>
<!-- body="start" -->
Cheryl writes :<br>
<p>
<p>
<i>&gt;One reason I began to doubt this doctrine myself was the fact that the NT</i><br>
<i>&gt;apostles did not seem to be concerned about attaining perfection. </i><br>
<p>
I'm sorry Cheryl but I just can not ignore the scripture when the Apostles,<br>
Paul and Jesus say : <br>
<p>
1 John 3:1 "My little children, these things I write unto you that you sin not."<br>
<p>
Matt 5:48 Be ye therefore perfect, even as your Father which is in heaven is<br>
          perfect. (KJV)<br>
<p>
2 Tim 3:16 All scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for<br>
           doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for instruction in<br>
           righteousness: (KJV)<br>
2 Tim 3:17 That the man of God may be perfect, throughly furnished unto all<br>
           good works. (KJV)<br>
<p>
Matt 19:26 But Jesus beheld them, and said unto them, With men this is<br>
           impossible; but with God all things are possible. (KJV)<br>
<p>
1 Thes 5:23 And the very God of peace sanctify you wholly; and I pray God your<br>
            whole spirit and soul and body be preserved blameless unto the<br>
            coming of our Lord Jesus Christ. (KJV)<br>
<p>
Heb 6:1 Therefore leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go<br>
        on unto perfection; not laying again the foundation of repentance from<br>
        dead works, and of faith toward God, (KJV)<br>
<p>
Jude 1:24 Now unto him that is able to keep you from falling, and to present<br>
          you faultless before the presence of his glory with exceeding joy,<br>
<p>
Rev 3:21 To him that overcometh will I grant to sit with me in my throne, even<br>
         as I also overcame, and am set down with my Father in his throne.<br>
<p>
Ruben.<br>
<!-- body="end" -->
